  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David in Old Age'
      title: David in Old Age
      number: 1
      content: '  Now King David was old, advanced in years; they covered him with
        clothes, but he could not get warm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So his servants said to him, \u201CLet a young virgin be found for
        my lord the king and let her attend him and become his nurse; let her lie
        against your chest, so that my lord the king may feel warm.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So they searched for a beautiful girl throughout the territory of
        Israel, and found Abishag the Shunammite, and brought her to the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The girl was very beautiful; and she became the king\u2019s nurse
        and served him, but the king was not intimate with her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Adonijah the son of [David\u2019s wife] Haggith exalted himself,
        saying, \u201CI [the eldest living son] will be king.\u201D So [following
        Absalom\u2019s example] he prepared for himself chariots and horsemen, and
        fifty men to run before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "His father [David] had never rebuked him at any time by asking, \u201CWhy
        have you done this?\u201D Adonijah was also a very handsome man, and he was
        born after Absalom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He had conferred with Joab the son of Zeruiah [David\u2019s half
        sister] and with Abiathar the priest; and they followed Adonijah and helped
        him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Zadok the priest, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, Nathan the prophet,
        Shimei, Rei, and David\u2019s most formidable warriors did not side with
        Adonijah [in his desire to become king].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Adonijah sacrificed sheep and oxen and fattened steers by the Stone
        of Zoheleth, which is beside [the well] En-rogel; and he invited all his
        brothers, the king\u2019s sons, and all the men of Judah, the king\u2019s
        servants [to this feast]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Nathan and Bathsheba'
      title: Nathan and Bathsheba
      number: 10
      content: 'But he did not invite Nathan the prophet, Benaiah, the most formidable
        warriors, or his brother Solomon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Nathan spoke to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon, \u201CHave
        you not heard that Adonijah the son of Haggith has become king, and David
        our lord does not know about it? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Come now, please let me advise you and save your life and the life
        of your son Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Go at once to King David and say to him, \u2018Did you not, my lord,
        O king, swear to your maidservant, saying, \u201CSolomon your son shall certainly
        be king after me, and he shall sit on my throne\u201D? Why then has Adonijah
        become king?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Behold, while you are still there speaking with the king, I will
        come in after you and confirm your words.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Bathsheba went to the king in his bedroom. Now the king was very
        old and weak, and Abishag the Shunammite was attending the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Bathsheba bowed down and paid respect to the king. And the king
        said, \u201CWhat do you wish?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "She said to him, \u201CMy lord, you swore by the Lord your God to
        your maidservant, saying, \u2018Solomon your son shall certainly be king
        after me and he shall sit on my throne.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But now, behold, Adonijah is [acting as] king; and now [as things
        stand], my lord the king, you do not know it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He has sacrificed oxen and fattened steers and sheep in abundance,
        and has invited all the king\u2019s sons and Abiathar the priest and Joab
        the commander of the army [to a feast], but he did not invite your servant
        Solomon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now as for you, my lord the king, the eyes of all Israel are on you
        [waiting for you] to tell them who shall sit on the throne of my lord the
        king after him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Otherwise it will come about when my lord the king lies down [in
        death] with his fathers, that I and my son Solomon will be considered political
        enemies.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'While she was still speaking with the king, Nathan the prophet came
        in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The king was told, \u201CHere is Nathan the prophet.\u201D And when
        he came before the king, he bowed before the king with his face to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Nathan said, \u201CMy lord the king, have you said, \u2018Adonijah
        shall be king after me, and he shall sit on my throne\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Because he has gone down today [to En-Rogel] and has sacrificed oxen
        and fattened steers and sheep in abundance, and has invited all the king\u2019s
        sons, the commanders of the army and Abiathar the priest [to this feast];
        and [right now] they are eating and drinking in his presence; and they say,
        \u2018Long live King Adonijah!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But he has not invited me, your servant, nor Zadok the priest, nor
        Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, nor your servant Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "If this thing has been done by my lord the king, why have you not
        shown your servants who shall sit on the throne of my lord the king after
        him?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "King David answered, \u201CCall Bathsheba to me.\u201D And she came
        into the king\u2019s presence and stood before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then the king swore an oath and said, \u201CAs the Lord lives, who
        has redeemed my soul from all distress, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "even as I swore to you by the Lord, the God of Israel, saying, \u2018Solomon
        your son shall certainly be king after me, and he shall sit on my throne
        in my place\u2019; I will indeed do so this very day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Bathsheba bowed down with her face to the ground, and laid herself
        face down before the king and said, \u201CMay my lord King David live forever!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then King David said, \u201CCall Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet,
        and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada to me.\u201D And they came before the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The king told them, \u201CTake the servants of your lord with you
        and have Solomon my son ride on my own mule, and bring him down to [the spring
        at] Gihon [in the Kidron Valley]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Let Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet anoint him there as king
        over Israel. Then blow the trumpet and say, \u2018Long live King Solomon!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Then you shall come up [to Jerusalem] after him, and he shall come
        and sit on my throne and he shall reign as king in my place; for I have appointed
        him to be ruler over Israel and Judah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Benaiah [the overseer of the king\u2019s bodyguards], the son of
        Jehoiada answered the king and said, \u201CAmen! (So be it!) May the Lord,
        the God of my lord the king, say so too. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: Solomon Anointed King'
      title: Solomon Anointed King
      number: 37
      content: "Just as the Lord has been with my lord the king, so may He be with
        Solomon, and make his throne greater than the throne of my lord King David!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "So Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada,
        the Cherethites, and the Pelethites [the king\u2019s bodyguards] went down
        [from Jerusalem] and had Solomon ride on King David\u2019s mule, and brought
        him to [the spring at] Gihon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Zadok the priest took a horn of [olive] oil from the [sacred] tent
        and anointed Solomon. They blew the trumpet, and all the people said, \u201CLong
        live King Solomon!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'All the people went up after him, and they were playing on flutes
        and rejoicing with great joy, so that the earth shook and seemed to burst
        open with their [joyful] sound.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Now Adonijah and all the guests who were with him heard it as they
        finished eating. When Joab heard the trumpet sound, he said, \u201CWhy is
        the city in such an uproar?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "While he was still speaking, behold, Jonathan the son of Abiathar
        the priest arrived. And Adonijah said, \u201CCome in, for you are a valiant
        and trustworthy man and you bring good news.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "But Jonathan replied to Adonijah, \u201CNo, on the contrary, our
        lord King David has made Solomon king! "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "The king has sent him with Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet,
        Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the Cherethites, and the Pelethites; and they
        have had him ride on the king\u2019s [own royal] mule. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Also, Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet have anointed him king
        in Gihon, and they have come up from there celebrating, so the city is in
        an uproar. This is the noise which you have heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Besides, Solomon has taken his seat on the throne of the kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Moreover, the king\u2019s servants came to bless (congratulate) our
        lord King David, saying, \u2018May your God make the name of Solomon better
        (more famous) than your name and make his throne greater than your throne.\u2019
        And the king bowed himself [before God] upon the bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "The king has also said this: \u2018Blessed be the Lord, the God of
        Israel, who has granted one [of my descendants] to sit on my throne today
        and allowed my eyes to see it.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Then all Adonijah\u2019s guests were terrified [of being branded
        as traitors] and stood up and left the feast, and each one went on his way. "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'And Adonijah feared Solomon, and he got up and went [to the tabernacle
        on Mt. Zion] and took hold of the horns of the altar [seeking asylum]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Now Solomon was told, \u201CBehold, Adonijah is afraid of King Solomon,
        and behold, he has grasped the horns of the altar [seeking God\u2019s protection],
        saying, \u2018King Solomon must swear to me today that he will not kill his
        servant with the sword.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "Solomon said, \u201CIf he [proves he] is a worthy man, not even one
        of his hairs shall fall to the ground; but if wickedness is found in him,
        he shall die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "So King Solomon sent [soldiers], and they brought Adonijah down from
        the altar [that was in front of the tabernacle]. And he came and bowed down
        to King Solomon, and Solomon said to him, \u201CGo to your house.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Charge to Solomon"
      title: "David\u2019s Charge to Solomon"
      number: 1
      content: "  When David\u2019s time to die approached, he gave instructions
        to Solomon his son, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI am going the way of all the earth [as dust to dust]. Be strong
        and prove yourself a man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Keep the charge of the Lord your God, [that is, fulfill your obligation
        to] walk in His ways, keep His statutes, His commandments, His precepts,
        and His testimonies, as it is written in the Law of Moses, so that you may
        succeed in everything that you do and wherever you turn, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "so that the Lord may fulfill His promise concerning me, saying, \u2018If
        your sons are careful regarding their way [of life], to walk before Me in
        truth with all their heart and mind and with all their soul, you shall not
        fail to have a man (descendant) on the throne of Israel.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now you also know what Joab the son of Zeruiah [my sister] did to
        me, and what he did to the two commanders of the armies of Israel, to Abner
        the son of Ner and to Amasa the son of Jether, [both of] whom he murdered;
        avenging the blood of war in [a time of] peace. And he put the [innocent]
        blood of war [of Abner and Amasa] on his belt that was around his waist,
        and on his sandals on his feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So act in accordance with your wisdom, but do not let his gray head
        go down to Sheol (the place of the dead) in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But be gracious and kind to the sons of Barzillai the Gileadite,
        and let them be among those who [have the honor to] eat at your table; for
        they met me [with kindness] when I fled from your brother Absalom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And look, you have with you Shimei the son of Gera, the Benjamite
        of Bahurim; he is the one who cursed me with a sinister curse the day I went
        to Mahanaim. But he came down to meet me at the Jordan [on my return], and
        I swore to him by the Lord, saying, \u2018I will not put you to death with
        the sword.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Death of David'
      title: Death of David
      number: 9
      content: "But now do not let him go unpunished, for you are a wise man; and
        you will know what to do to him, and you will bring his gray head down to
        Sheol [covered] with blood.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So David lay down with his fathers [in death] and was buried in the
        City of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The time that David reigned over Israel was forty years: he reigned
        seven years in Hebron and thirty-three years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Solomon sat on the throne of David his father, and his kingdom
        was firmly established.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now Adonijah the son of [David and] Haggith came to Bathsheba the
        mother of Solomon. She said, \u201CDo you come in peace?\u201D And he said,
        \u201CIn peace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he said, \u201CI have something to say to you.\u201D And she
        said, \u201CSpeak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So he said, \u201CYou know that the kingdom belonged to me [as the
        eldest living son] and all Israel looked to me and expected me to be king.
        However, the kingdom has passed [from me] and became my brother\u2019s, for
        it was his from the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So now I am making one request of you; do not refuse me.\u201D And
        she said to him, \u201CSpeak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He said, \u201CPlease speak to King Solomon, for he will not refuse
        you; ask that he may give me Abishag the Shunammite as a wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Adonijah Executed'
      title: Adonijah Executed
      number: 18
      content: "Bathsheba replied, \u201CVery well; I will speak to the king for
        you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So Bathsheba went to King Solomon to speak to him for Adonijah. And
        the king rose to meet her, bowed before her, and sat down on his throne;
        then he had a throne set for her, the king\u2019s mother, and she sat on
        his right. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then she said, \u201CI am making one small request of you; do not
        refuse me.\u201D And the king said to her, \u201CAsk, my mother, for I will
        not refuse you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So she said, \u201CLet Abishag the Shunammite be given to your brother
        Adonijah as a wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "King Solomon answered and said to his mother, \u201CAnd why are you
        asking for Abishag the Shunammite for Adonijah? Ask the kingdom for him also\u2014since
        he is my older brother\u2014[ask it] for him and for Abiathar the priest
        and Joab the son of Zeruiah [his supporters]!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then King Solomon swore by the Lord, saying, \u201CMay God do the
        same to me, and more also, if Adonijah has not requested this [deplorable]
        thing against his own life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So now, as the Lord lives, who has established me and set me on the
        throne of David my father, and who has made me a house as He promised, Adonijah
        shall indeed be put to death today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So King Solomon sent Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and he struck Adonijah
        and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then the king said to Abiathar the priest, \u201CGo to Anathoth to
        your own fields, for you certainly deserve to die; but I will not put you
        to death this day, because you carried the ark of the Lord God before my
        father David, and you suffered everything that my father endured.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Joab Executed'
      title: Joab Executed
      number: 27
      content: 'So Solomon dismissed Abiathar [a descendant of Eli] from being priest
        to the Lord, fulfilling the word of the Lord, which He had spoken concerning
        the house (descendants) of Eli in Shiloh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now the news reached Joab, for Joab had supported and followed Adonijah,
        although he had not followed Absalom. So Joab fled to the [sacred] tent of
        the Lord and took hold of the horns of the altar [to seek asylum]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "King Solomon was told that Joab had fled to the tent of the Lord
        and was at that moment beside the altar. Then Solomon sent Benaiah the son
        of Jehoiada, saying, \u201CGo, strike him down.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So Benaiah came to the tent of the Lord and told Joab, \u201CThis
        is what the king commands, \u2018Come out of there.\u2019\u2009\u201D But
        Joab said, \u201CNo, for I will die here.\u201D Then Benaiah brought word
        to the king again, saying, \u201CThis is what Joab said, and this is how
        he answered me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "The king said to him, \u201CDo as he has said. Strike him down and
        bury him, so that you may remove from me and from my father\u2019s house
        the innocent blood which Joab shed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The Lord will return his bloody deeds upon his own head, because
        he struck down two men more righteous and honorable than he and killed them
        with the sword, without my father David knowing: Abner the son of Ner, commander
        of the army of Israel, and Amasa the son of Jether, commander of the army
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So shall their blood return on the head of Joab and the heads of
        his descendants forever. But for David, his descendants, his house, and his
        throne, may there be peace from the Lord forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'So Benaiah the son of Jehoiada went up [to the tabernacle] and struck
        and killed Joab, and he was buried at his own house in the wilderness [of
        Judah]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: Shimei Executed'
      title: Shimei Executed
      number: 35
      content: "The king appointed Benaiah the son of Jehoiada over the army in Joab\u2019s
        place, and appointed Zadok the priest in place of Abiathar.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Now the king sent word and called for Shimei and said to him, \u201CBuild
        yourself a house in Jerusalem and live there. Do not go from there to any
        other place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "For on the day you leave and cross over the Brook Kidron, know for
        certain that you shall surely die; your blood shall be on your own head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Shimei said to the king, \u201CThe word (ruling) is good. As my lord
        the king has said, so will your servant do.\u201D So Shimei lived in Jerusalem
        for many days.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But it happened after three years, that two of Shimei\u2019s servants
        ran away to Achish the son of Maacah, the king of Gath. And Shimei was told,
        \u201CBehold, your [runaway] servants are in Gath.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'So Shimei arose, saddled his donkey, and went to Gath to [King] Achish
        to look for his servants. And Shimei went and brought them back from Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Now Solomon was told that Shimei had gone from Jerusalem to Gath,
        and had returned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "So the king sent word and called for Shimei and said to him, \u201CDid
        I not make you swear by the Lord and solemnly warn you, saying, \u2018Know
        for certain that on the day you leave [Jerusalem] and go anywhere, you shall
        surely die\u2019? And you said to me, \u2018The word (ruling) I have heard
        is good.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Why then have you not kept the oath of the Lord, and the command
        which I gave you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "The king also said to Shimei, \u201CYou are aware in your own heart
        of all the evil you did to my father David; so the Lord shall return your
        evil on your own head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "But King Solomon shall be blessed, and the throne of David shall
        be established before the Lord forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: So the king commanded Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and he went out
        and struck down Shimei, and he died.  So the kingdom was established in the
        hands of Solomon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Solomon\u2019s Rule Consolidated"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Rule Consolidated"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Solomon became a son-in-law to Pharaoh king of Egypt [and formed
        an alliance] by taking Pharaoh\u2019s daughter [in marriage]. He brought
        her to the City of David [where she remained temporarily] until he had finished
        building his own house (palace) and the house of the Lord and the wall around
        Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But [in the meantime] the people were still sacrificing [to God]
        on the high places (hilltops) [as the pagans did to their idols], for there
        was no [permanent] house yet built for the Name of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Solomon loved the Lord, walking [at first] in the statutes of
        David his father, except [for the fact that] he sacrificed and burned incense
        in the high places [ignoring the law that required all sacrifices to be offered
        at the tabernacle]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The king went to Gibeon [near Jerusalem, where the tabernacle and
        the bronze altar stood] to sacrifice there, for that was the great high place.
        Solomon offered a thousand burnt offerings on that altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: "5: Solomon\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 5
      content: "In Gibeon the Lord appeared to Solomon in a dream at night; and God
        said, \u201CAsk [Me] what I shall give you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Solomon said, \u201CYou have shown Your servant David my father
        great lovingkindness, because he walked before You in faithfulness and righteousness
        and with uprightness of heart toward You; and You have kept for him this
        great lovingkindness, in that You have given him a son to sit on his throne,
        as it is today. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So now, O Lord my God, You have made Your servant king in place of
        David my father; and as for me, I am but a little boy [in wisdom and experience];
        I do not know how to go out or come in [that is, how to conduct business
        as a king]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Your servant is among Your people whom You have chosen, a great people
        who are too many to be numbered or counted. '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: God\u2019s Answer"
      title: "God\u2019s Answer"
      number: 9
      content: "So give Your servant an understanding mind and a hearing heart [with
        which] to judge Your people, so that I may discern between good and evil.
        For who is able to judge and rule this great people of Yours?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now it pleased the Lord that Solomon had asked this thing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "God said to him, \u201CBecause you have asked this and have not asked
        for yourself a long life nor for wealth, nor for the lives of your enemies,
        but have asked for yourself understanding to recognize justice, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'behold, I have done as you asked. I have given you a wise and discerning
        heart (mind), so that no one before you was your equal, nor shall anyone
        equal to you arise after you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I have also given you what you have not asked, both wealth and honor,
        so that there will not be anyone equal to you among the kings, for all your
        days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "If you walk in My ways, keeping My statutes and My commandments,
        as your father David did, then I will lengthen your days.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Solomon Wisely Judges'
      title: Solomon Wisely Judges
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Solomon awoke, and he realized that it was a dream. He came
        [back] to Jerusalem and stood before the ark of the covenant of the Lord;
        he offered burnt offerings and peace offerings, and he prepared a feast for
        all his servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then two women who were prostitutes came to the king and stood before
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the one woman said, \u201CO my lord, this woman and I live in
        the same house; and I gave birth to a child while she was in the house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And on the third day after I gave birth, this woman also gave birth.
        And we were [alone] together; no one else was with us in the house, just
        we two. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now this woman\u2019s son died during the night, because she lay
        on him [and smothered him]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So she got up in the middle of the night and took my son from [his
        place] beside me while your maidservant was asleep, and laid him on her bosom,
        and laid her dead son on my bosom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "When I got up in the morning to nurse my son, behold, he was dead.
        But when I examined him carefully in the morning, behold, it was not my son,
        the one whom I had borne.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the other woman said, \u201CNo! For my son is the one who is
        living, and your son is the dead one.\u201D But the first woman said, \u201CNo!
        For your son is the dead one, and my son is the living one.\u201D [This is
        how] they were speaking before the king.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CThis woman says, \u2018This is my son,
        the one who is alive, and your son is the dead one\u2019; and the other woman
        says, \u2018No! For your son is the dead one, and my son is the one who is
        alive.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CBring me a sword.\u201D So they brought
        a sword before the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CCut the living child in two, and give half
        to the one [woman] and half to the other.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then the woman whose child was the living one spoke to the king,
        for she was deeply moved over her son, \u201CO my lord, give her the living
        child, and by no means kill him.\u201D But the other said, \u201CHe shall
        be neither mine nor yours; cut him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CGive the first woman [who is pleading for
        his life] the living child, and by no means kill him. She is his mother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: When all [the people of] Israel heard about the judgment which the
        king had made, they [were in awe and reverently] feared the king, for they
        saw that the wisdom of God was within him to administer justice.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Solomon\u2019s Officials"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Officials"
      number: 1
      content: '  King Solomon was king over all [the people of] Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'These were his [chief] officials: Azariah the son of Zadok was the
        high priest; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Elihoreph and Ahijah the sons of Shisha, were scribes; Jehoshaphat
        the son of Ahilud was the recorder [of important events]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was in command of the army; Zadok and
        Abiathar were priests; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Azariah the son of Nathan was in charge of the deputies; Zabud the
        son of Nathan was priest and was the king\u2019s friend [and trusted advisor]; "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Ahishar was in charge of the household (palace); and Adoniram the
        son of Abda was in charge of the forced labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Solomon had twelve deputies over all Israel, who secured provisions
        for the king and his household; each man had to provide for a month in the
        year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'These were their names: Ben-hur, in the hill country of [the tribe
        of] Ephraim; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ben-deker in Makaz and Shaalbim and Beth-shemesh and Elon-beth-hanan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Ben-hesed, in Arubboth (to him belonged Socoh and all the land of
        Hepher); '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Ben-abinadab, in all the hills of Dor (Taphath, Solomon\u2019s daughter,
        was his wife); "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Baana the son of Ahilud, in Taanach, Megiddo, and all Beth-shean
        which is beside Zarethan below Jezreel, from Beth-shean to Abel-meholah as
        far as beyond Jokmeam; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Ben-geber, in Ramoth-gilead (the villages of Jair the son of Manasseh,
        which are in Gilead belonged to him, also the region of Argob, which is in
        Bashan, sixty great cities with walls and bronze bars); '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Ahinadab the son of Iddo, in Mahanaim; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Ahimaaz, in [the tribe of] Naphtali (he also married Basemath, Solomon\u2019s
        daughter); "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Baana the son of Hushai, in [the tribe of] Asher and Bealoth; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Jehoshaphat the son of Paruah, in [the tribe of] Issachar; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Shimei the son of Ela, in [the tribe of] Benjamin; '
      comments: []
    - name: "19: Solomon\u2019s Power, Wealth and Wisdom"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Power, Wealth and Wisdom"
      number: 19
      content: 'Geber the son of Uri, in the land of Gilead, the country of Sihon
        king of the Amorites and of Og king of Bashan; and he was the only officer
        who was in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '[The people of] Judah and Israel were as numerous as the sand that
        is in abundance by the sea; they were eating and drinking and rejoicing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Now Solomon reigned over all the kingdoms from the [Euphrates]
        River to the land of the Philistines and to the border of Egypt; they brought
        tribute (money) and served Solomon all the days of his life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Solomon\u2019s food [for the royal household] for one day was thirty
        kors of finely milled flour, sixty kors of wheat flour, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'ten fat oxen, twenty pasture-fed oxen, a hundred sheep not counting
        fallow deer, gazelles, roebucks, and fattened fowl. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For he was ruling over everything west of the [Euphrates] River,
        from Tiphsah to Gaza, over all the kings west of the [Euphrates] River; and
        he had peace on all sides around him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Judah and Israel lived in security, every man under his vine and
        fig tree [in peace and prosperity], from Dan [in the north] to Beersheba
        [in the south], during all the days of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Solomon also had 40,000 stalls of horses for his chariots, and 12,000
        horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Those deputies provided food for King Solomon and for all [the staff]
        who came to King Solomon\u2019s table, each in his month; they let nothing
        be lacking. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They also brought the barley and straw for the horses and swift steeds
        (warhorses, chargers) to the place where it was needed, each man according
        to his assignment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now God gave Solomon [exceptional] wisdom and very great discernment
        and breadth of mind, like the sand of the seashore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Solomon\u2019s wisdom surpassed the wisdom of all the sons of the
        east and all the wisdom of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For he was wiser than all [other] men, [wiser] than Ethan the Ezrahite,
        and Heman, Calcol, and Darda, the sons of Mahol. His fame was known in all
        the surrounding nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He also spoke 3,000 proverbs, and his songs were 1,005. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He spoke of trees, from the cedar which is in Lebanon to the hyssop
        [vine] that grows on the wall; he spoke also of animals, of birds, of creeping
        things, and fish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: People came from all the peoples (nations) to hear the wisdom of Solomon,
        and from all the kings of the earth who had heard of his wisdom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Alliance with King Hiram'
      title: Alliance with King Hiram
      number: 1
      content: '  Hiram king of Tyre sent his servants to Solomon when he heard that
        they had anointed him king in place of his father, for Hiram had always been
        a friend of David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Solomon sent word to Hiram, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CYou know that David my father could not build a house (temple)
        for the Name (Presence) of the Lord his God because of the wars which surrounded
        him, until the Lord put his enemies under his feet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But now that the Lord my God has given me rest [from war] on every
        side, there is neither adversary nor misfortune [confronting me]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Behold, I intend to build a house (temple) to the Name of the Lord
        my God, just as the Lord said to my father David: \u2018Your son whom I will
        put on your throne in your place shall build the house for My Name and Presence.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So now, command that they cut cedar trees from Lebanon for me, and
        my servants will join your servants, and I will give you whatever wages you
        set for your servants. For you know that there is no one among us who knows
        how to cut timber like the men of Sidon.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When Hiram heard the words of Solomon, he rejoiced greatly and said,
        \u201CBlessed be the Lord this day, who has given David a wise son [to be
        king] over this great people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Hiram sent word to Solomon, saying, \u201CI have heard the message
        which you sent to me; I will do everything you wish concerning the cedar
        and cypress timber. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "My servants will bring the logs down from Lebanon to the [Mediterranean]
        sea, and I will have them made into rafts to go by sea to the place (port)
        that you direct me; then I will have them broken up there, and you shall
        carry them away. Then you shall return the favor by providing food for my
        household.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Hiram gave Solomon all the cedar and cypress timber he desired, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and Solomon gave Hiram 20,000 kors of wheat as food for his household,
        and 20 kors of pure [olive] oil. Solomon gave all these to Hiram each year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Conscription of Laborers'
      title: Conscription of Laborers
      number: 12
      content: 'The Lord gave Solomon wisdom, just as He promised him; and there
        was peace between Hiram and Solomon, and the two of them made a treaty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'King Solomon levied forced laborers from all Israel; and the forced
        laborers numbered 30,000 men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He sent them to Lebanon, 10,000 a month in shifts; one month they
        were in Lebanon and two months at home. Adoniram was in charge of the forced
        laborers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Solomon had 70,000 burden bearers (transporters) and 80,000 stonemasons
        in the hill country [of Judah], '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "besides Solomon\u2019s 3,300 chief deputies who were in charge of
        the project and who were in charge of the people doing the work. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The king gave orders, and they quarried great stones, valuable stones,
        to lay the foundation of the house (temple) with cut stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Solomon\u2019s builders and Hiram\u2019s builders and the men
        of Gebal cut and chiseled the stones, and prepared the timber and the stones
        to build the house (temple)."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Building of the Temple'
      title: The Building of the Temple
      number: 1
      content: "    Now it came about in the four hundred and eightieth year after
        the Israelites came out of the land of Egypt, in the fourth year of Solomon\u2019s
        reign over Israel, in the month of Ziv (April-May) which is the second month,
        that he began to build the Lord\u2019s house (temple). "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The length of the house which King Solomon built for the Lord was
        sixty cubits (90 ft.), its width twenty (30 ft.), and its height thirty cubits
        (45 ft.). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The porch in front of the main room of the house (temple) was twenty
        cubits long, corresponding to the width of the house, and its depth in front
        of the house was ten cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He also made framed (artistic) window openings for the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Against the wall of the house he built extensions around the walls
        of the house, around both the main room (Holy Place) and the Holy of Holies;
        and he made side chambers all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The lowest story was five cubits wide, the middle was six cubits
        wide, and the third was seven cubits wide; for he made offsets (niches) in
        the walls all around on the outside of the house so that the supporting beams
        would not be inserted into the walls of the house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'While it was being built, the house was built of stone prepared and
        finished (precut) at the quarry, and no hammer, axe, or iron tool of any
        kind was heard in the house while it was under construction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The entrance to the lowest side chamber was on the right [or south]
        side of the house; and they would go up winding stairs to the middle [level],
        and from the middle to the third. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Solomon built the house (temple) and finished it, and roofed the
        house with beams and boards of cedar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then he built the extensions [of rooms] against the entire house,
        each [story] five cubits high; and they were attached to the house with timbers
        of cedar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now the word of the Lord came to Solomon, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CConcerning this house which you are building, if you will walk
        in My statutes and execute My precepts and keep all My commandments by walking
        in them, then I will carry out My word (promises) with you which I made to
        David your father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I will dwell among the sons (descendants) of Israel, and will not
        abandon My people Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Solomon built the house (temple) and finished it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He built the walls of the interior of the house [that is, the Holy
        Place and the Holy of Holies] with boards of cedar, from the floor of the
        house to the rafters of the ceiling. He overlaid the interior with wood,
        and he overlaid the floor of the house with boards of cypress. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He built twenty cubits on the rear of the house with boards of cedar
        from the floor to the ceiling; he built its interior as the [inner] sanctuary,
        the Holy of Holies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The [rest of the] house, that is, the temple in front of the Holy
        of Holies, was forty cubits long. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The cedar on the house within had wood carvings in the shape of gourds
        and open flowers. Everything was cedar; no stone was visible. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then he prepared the Holy of Holies within the house in order to
        put the ark of the covenant of the Lord there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The Holy of Holies was twenty cubits in length, twenty cubits in
        width, and twenty cubits in height (a cube), and he overlaid it with pure
        gold. He also overlaid the cedar altar [with gold]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Solomon overlaid the interior of the house with pure gold, and he
        drew chains of gold across the front of the Holy of Holies (inner sanctuary),
        and he overlaid it with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then he overlaid the entire house with gold, until the whole house
        was finished. He also overlaid the entire [incense] altar which was by the
        Holy of Holies with gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Within the Holy of Holies he made two cherubim (sculptured figures)
        of olive wood, each ten cubits high. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'One wing of the cherub was five cubits long, and the other wing was
        also five cubits long; it was ten cubits from the tip of one wing to the
        tip of the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The [wingspan of the] other cherub was also ten cubits. The measurements
        and cut (shape) of the two cherubim were the same; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'the height of the one cherub was ten cubits, as was the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He put the cherubim [above the ark] inside the innermost room of
        the house, and their wings were spread out so that the wing of the one touched
        one wall, and the wing of the other cherub was touching the other wall; and
        their inner wings were touching each other in the middle of the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Solomon also overlaid the cherubim with gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He carved all the walls of the house all around with carved engravings
        of cherubim, palm-shaped decorations, and open flowers, [both] the inner
        and the outer sanctuaries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'He overlaid the floor of the house with gold, [both] the inner and
        outer sanctuaries.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For the entrance of the Holy of Holies he made two [folding] doors
        of olive wood, the lintel (header above the door) and five-sided doorposts
        (frames). '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So he made two doors of olive wood, and he carved on them carvings
        of cherubim, palm-shaped decorations, and open flowers; and overlaid them
        with gold; and he hammered out overlays of gold on the cherubim and palm
        decorations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Also he made for the entrance of the [outer] sanctuary (the Holy
        Place) four-sided doorposts (frames) of olive wood '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'and two doors of cypress wood; the two leaves of the one door turned
        on pivots and were folding, and the two leaves of the other door also turned
        on pivots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'He carved cherubim, palm-shaped decorations, and open flowers on
        the doors, and overlaid them with gold evenly applied on the carved work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'He built the inner courtyard with three rows of cut stone and a row
        of cedar beams.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "In the fourth year [of King Solomon\u2019s reign] the foundation
        of the Lord\u2019s house was laid, in the [second] month, Ziv (April-May). "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "In the eleventh year [of King Solomon\u2019s reign] in the month
        of Bul (October-November), that is, the eighth month, the house was finished
        throughout all its parts and in accordance with all its specifications. So
        he built it in seven years."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Solomon\u2019s Palace"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Palace"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Solomon built his own house (palace) in thirteen years, and
        he finished all of his house [in that time]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He also built the House of the Forest of Lebanon; its length was
        a hundred cubits (150 ft.), its width fifty cubits (75 ft.), and its height
        thirty cubits (45 ft.), upon four rows of cedar pillars, with cedar beams
        upon the pillars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And it was covered with cedar [as a roof] on the supporting beams
        that were upon the forty-five pillars, fifteen in each row. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'There were artistic window frames in three rows, and window was opposite
        window in three tiers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All the doorways and doorposts [and windows] had squared [artistic]
        frames, and window was opposite window in three tiers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He also made the Hall of Pillars; its length was fifty cubits (75
        ft.) and its width thirty cubits (45 ft.). There was a porch in front, and
        pillars and a threshold in front of them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He made the hall for the throne where he was to judge, the Hall of
        Judgment; it was paneled with cedar from [one] floor to [another] floor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "His house where he was to live, the other courtyard behind the hall,
        was of similar workmanship. Solomon also made a house like this hall for
        Pharaoh\u2019s daughter, whom he had married.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'All these were of expensive stones, of stone cut according to measure,
        sawed with saws, inside and outside; even from the foundation to the coping,
        and from the outside to the great courtyard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The foundation was of expensive stones, large stones, stones of ten
        cubits and stones of eight cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And above [the foundation] were expensive stones, stones cut according
        to measure, and cedar. '
      comments: []
    - name: "12: Hiram\u2019s Work in the Temple"
      title: "Hiram\u2019s Work in the Temple"
      number: 12
      content: 'So the great courtyard all around had three rows of cut stone and
        a row of cedar beams like the inner courtyard of the house of the Lord, and
        the porch of the house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now King Solomon sent word and brought Hiram [a skilled craftsman]
        from Tyre. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He was the son of a widow from the tribe of Naphtali, and his father
        was a man of Tyre, a craftsman in bronze. Hiram was filled with wisdom, understanding,
        and skill for doing any [kind of] work in bronze. So he came to King Solomon
        and did all his [bronze] work.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He cast the two pillars of bronze; the one pillar was eighteen cubits
        high, and a [measuring] line of twelve cubits measured the circumference
        of both. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He also made two capitals (crowns) of cast bronze to put on the tops
        of the pillars; the height of one capital was five cubits, and the height
        of the other capital was five cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'There were nets of network (lattice-work) and twisted threads (wreaths)
        of chainwork for the capitals which were on the tops of the pillars, seven
        for one capital and seven for the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So Hiram made the pillars [in this manner], and two rows around on
        the one network to cover the capitals which were on the top of the pomegranates;
        and he did the same for the other capital. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The capitals which were upon the top of the pillars in the porch
        were of lily work (design), four cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The capitals were on the two pillars and also above and close to
        the rounded projection which was beside the network. There were two hundred
        pomegranates in rows around both capitals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Hiram set up the pillars at the porch of the temple; he set up the
        right pillar and named it Jachin (may he establish), and he set up the left
        pillar and named it Boaz (in it is strength). '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'On the tops of the pillars was lily work (design). So the work of
        the pillars was finished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now he made the Sea (basin) of cast metal, ten cubits from brim to
        brim, circular in form, five cubits high and thirty cubits in circumference. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Under its brim were gourds encircling it ten to a cubit, completely
        surrounding the Sea; the gourds were in two rows, cast in one piece with
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'It stood on twelve oxen, three facing north, three west, three south,
        and three east; the Sea was set on top of them, and all their rear parts
        pointed inward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'It was a hand width thick, and its brim was made like the brim of
        a cup, like a lily blossom. It held two thousand baths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then Hiram made ten bronze stands [for smaller basins]; the length
        of each stand was four cubits, its width was four cubits and its height was
        three cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'This was the design of the stands: they had borders between the frames. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'On the borders between the frames were lions, oxen, and cherubim;
        and on the frames there was a pedestal above. Beneath the lions and oxen
        were borders of hanging work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now each stand had four bronze wheels with bronze axles, and its
        four feet had supports [for a basin]. Beneath the basin were cast supports
        with borders at each side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Its opening inside the crown at the top measured a cubit, and its
        opening was round like the design of a pedestal, a cubit and a half. Also
        on its opening were carvings, and their borders were square, not round. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Underneath the borders were four wheels, and the axles of the wheels
        were on the stand. And the height of a wheel was a cubit and a half. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The wheels were made like a chariot wheel: their axles, their rims,
        their spokes, and their hubs were all cast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Now there were four supports at the four corners of each stand; the
        supports were part of the stand itself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'On the top of the stand there was a circular piece half a cubit high,
        and on the top of the stand its supports and borders were part of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And on the surface of its supports and its borders Hiram engraved
        cherubim, lions, and palm-shaped decorations, according to the [available]
        space for each, with borders all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'He made the ten stands like this: they all had one casting, one measure,
        and one form.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then he made ten basins of bronze; each basin held forty baths and
        was four cubits, and there was one basin on each of the ten stands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Then he placed the bases, five on the right [or south] side of the
        house and five on the left [or north] side; and he set the Sea [of cast metal]
        on the right side of the house toward the southeast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Now Hiram made the basins and the shovels and the bowls. So Hiram
        finished all the work which he did for King Solomon on the house of the Lord: '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'the two pillars and the [two] bowls of the capitals which were on
        the top of the two pillars, and the two networks to cover the two bowls of
        the capitals which were on top of the pillars; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'and the four hundred pomegranates for the two networks, two rows
        of pomegranates for each network to cover the two bowls of the capitals that
        were on the tops of the pillars; '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'the ten stands and the ten basins on the stands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'one Sea (basin), and the twelve oxen under the Sea; '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'the pails, the shovels, and the bowls; all these utensils which Hiram
        made for King Solomon in the house of the Lord were of polished bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'In the plain of the Jordan [River] the king cast them, in the clay
        ground between Succoth and Zarethan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Solomon left all the utensils unweighed, because there were so many;
        the weight of the bronze could not be determined.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Solomon made all the [other] furniture which was in the house of
        the Lord: the [incense] altar of gold; the table of gold on which was the
        bread of the Presence; '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'the lampstands of pure gold, five on the right side and five on the
        left, in front of the Holy of Holies (inner sanctuary); with the flowers,
        the lamps, and the tongs of gold; '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "the cups, snuffers, bowls, spoons, firepans\u2014of pure gold; and
        the hinges of gold [both] for the doors of the inner house, the Holy of Holies,
        and for the doors of the house, the main room [the Holy Place].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "So all the work that King Solomon did on the house of the Lord was
        completed. Solomon brought in the things which David his father had dedicated\u2014the
        silver, the gold, and the utensils\u2014and he put them in the treasuries
        of the Lord\u2019s house."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark Brought into the Temple'
      title: The Ark Brought into the Temple
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Solomon assembled the elders of Israel and all the heads of
        the tribes, the leaders of the fathers\u2019 households of the sons of Israel,
        to King Solomon in Jerusalem, to bring up the ark of the covenant of the
        Lord from the City of David, which is Zion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'All the men of Israel assembled before King Solomon at the feast
        in the month of Ethanim (September-October), that is, the seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All the elders of Israel came, and the priests carried the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They brought up the ark of the Lord and the Tent of Meeting and all
        the holy utensils that were in the tent; the priests and the Levites brought
        them up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'King Solomon and all the congregation of Israel, who had assembled
        before him, were with him before the ark, sacrificing sheep and oxen, so
        many that they could not be counted or numbered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the priests brought the ark of the covenant of the Lord to its
        place, into the inner sanctuary of the house, into the Holy of Holies, under
        the wings of the cherubim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the cherubim spread their two wings over the place of the ark,
        and the cherubim covered the ark and its [carrying] poles from above. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The poles were so long that the ends of the poles were visible from
        the Holy Place that was in front of the Holy of Holies, but they were not
        visible from the outside; they are there to this day (the date of this writing). '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'There was nothing in the ark except the two tablets of stone which
        Moses put there at Horeb (Sinai), where the Lord made a covenant with the
        Israelites when they came out of the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now it happened that when the priests had come out of the Holy Place,
        the cloud filled the Lord\u2019s house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Solomon Addresses the People'
      title: Solomon Addresses the People
      number: 11
      content: "so the priests could not stand [in their positions] to minister because
        of the cloud, for the glory and brilliance of the Lord had filled the Lord\u2019s
        house (temple).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Solomon said,\u201CThe Lord has said that He would dwell in
        the thick darkness [of the cloud].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I have certainly built You a lofty house,A place for You to dwell
        in forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the king turned around and blessed all the assembly of Israel,
        while all the assembly of Israel was standing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He said, \u201CBlessed be the Lord, the God of Israel, who spoke
        with His mouth to my father David and has fulfilled it with His hand, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018Since the day that I brought My people Israel out of Egypt,
        I did not choose a [particular] city out of all the tribes of Israel in which
        to build a house so that My Name (Presence) would be in it, but I chose David
        to be over My people Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now it was [determined] in the heart of my father David to build
        a house (temple) for the Name of the Lord, the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But the Lord said to my father David, \u2018Because it was in your
        heart to build a house for My Name, you did well, in that it was in your
        heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Nevertheless, you shall not build the house, but your son, who shall
        be born to you, it is he who shall build it for My Name [and My Presence].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now the Lord has fulfilled His word which He spoke; I have risen
        in the place of my father David and have taken my seat on the throne of Israel,
        just as the Lord promised, and have built the house (temple) for the Name
        of the Lord, the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Prayer of Dedication'
      title: The Prayer of Dedication
      number: 21
      content: "There I have made a place [in the Holy of Holies] for the ark, in
        which is the covenant (solemn agreement) of the Lord, which He made with
        our fathers when He brought them out of the land of Egypt.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then Solomon stood [in the courtyard] before the altar of the Lord
        in the presence of all the assembly of Israel and spread out his hands toward
        heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He said, \u201CO Lord, the God of Israel, there is no God like You
        in heaven above or on earth below, who keeps the covenant and shows lovingkindness
        to Your servants who walk before You with all their heart; "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You who have kept what You promised to Your servant my father David.
        You have spoken with Your mouth and have fulfilled Your word with Your hand,
        as it is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now therefore, O Lord, the God of Israel, keep for Your servant my
        father David that which You promised him when You said, \u2018You shall not
        be without a man (descendant) to sit on the throne of Israel, if only your
        sons take heed to their way [of life] to walk before Me [according to my
        laws] as you have done.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now, O God of Israel, please let Your word which You have spoken
        to Your servant David my father be confirmed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But will God indeed dwell on the earth? Behold, heaven and the highest
        heaven cannot contain You; how much less this house which I have built! '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Yet graciously consider the prayer of Your servant and his supplication,
        O Lord my God, to listen to the [loud] cry and to the prayer which Your servant
        prays before You today; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "that Your eyes may be open toward this house night and day, toward
        the place of which You have said, \u2018My Name (Presence) shall be there,\u2019
        that You may listen to the prayer which Your servant shall pray toward this
        place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Listen to the prayer of Your servant and of Your people Israel which
        they pray toward this place. Hear in heaven, Your dwelling place; hear and
        forgive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CIf a man sins against his neighbor and is made to take an oath
        [of innocence] and he comes to take the oath before Your altar in this house
        (temple), "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'then hear from heaven and act and judge Your servants, condemning
        the wicked by bringing his guilt on his own head, and justifying the righteous
        by rewarding him in accordance with his righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CWhen Your people Israel are defeated before an enemy because
        they have sinned against You, and then they turn to You again and praise
        Your Name and pray and ask for Your favor and compassion in this house (temple), "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'then hear in heaven, and forgive the sin of Your people Israel, and
        bring them back to the land which You gave their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CWhen the heavens are shut up and there is no rain because they
        have sinned against You, and they pray toward this place and praise Your
        name and turn from their sin when You afflict them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'then hear in heaven and forgive the sin of Your servants and of Your
        people Israel; indeed, teach them the good way in which they should walk
        (live). And send rain on Your land which You have given to Your people as
        an inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "\u201CIf there is famine in the land, or if there is pestilence (plague),
        blight, mildew, migratory locusts, or grasshoppers, if their enemy besieges
        them in the land of their cities, whatever affliction or plague, whatever
        sickness [there is], "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'whatever prayer or pleading is made by any individual, or by Your
        people Israel, each knowing the affliction of his own heart, and spreading
        his hands out toward this house; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'then hear in heaven Your dwelling place, and forgive and act and
        give to each according to his ways, whose heart (mind) You know, for You
        and You alone know the hearts of all the children of men, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'so that they may fear You [with reverence and awe] all the days that
        they live in the land which You have given to our fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CMoreover, concerning a foreigner who is not of Your people
        Israel, but comes from a far (distant) country for the sake of Your name
        [to plead with You] "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: '(for they will hear of Your great name, Your strong hand [of power],
        and outstretched arm); when he comes and prays toward this house (temple), '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'hear in heaven, Your dwelling place, and do according to all for
        which the foreigner calls upon (prays to) You, so that all peoples of the
        earth may know Your name and fear You [with reverence and awe], as do Your
        people Israel, and that they may know [without any doubt] that this house
        which I have built is called by Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CWhen Your people go out to battle against their enemy, by whatever
        way You send them, and they pray to the Lord toward the city which You have
        chosen and the house that I have built for Your Name and Presence, "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'then hear in heaven their prayer and their pleading, and maintain
        their right and defend their cause.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "\u201CWhen they sin against You (for there is no man who does not
        sin) and You are angry with them and hand them over to the enemy, so that
        they are carried away captive to the enemy\u2019s land, [whether] far away
        or near; "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "if they take it to heart in the land where they have been taken captive,
        and they repent and pray to You in the land of their captors, saying, \u2018We
        have sinned and done wrong and we have acted wickedly;\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'if they return to You with all their heart and with all their soul
        in the land of their enemies who have taken them captive, and they pray to
        You toward their land [of Israel] which You gave to their fathers, the city
        [of Jerusalem] which You have chosen, and the house which I have built for
        Your Name and Presence; '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'then hear their prayer and their supplication in heaven Your dwelling
        place, and maintain their right and defend their cause, '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'and forgive Your people who have sinned against You and all the transgressions
        which they have committed against You, and make them objects of compassion
        before their captors, that they will be merciful to them '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: '(for they are Your people and Your heritage, whom You brought out
        of Egypt, from the midst of the iron furnace [of slavery and oppression]), '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'that Your eyes may be open to the supplication of Your servant and
        to the supplication of Your people Israel, to listen to them and be attentive
        to them whenever they call to You. '
      comments: []
    - name: "53: Solomon\u2019s Benediction"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Benediction"
      number: 53
      content: "For You singled them out from all the peoples of the earth as Your
        heritage, just as You declared through Moses Your servant, when You brought
        our fathers out of Egypt, O Lord God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "When Solomon finished offering this entire prayer and supplication
        to the Lord, he arose from before the Lord\u2019s altar, where he had knelt
        down with his hands stretched toward heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'And he stood and blessed all the assembly of Israel with a loud voice,
        saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "\u201CBlessed be the Lord, who has given rest to His people Israel,
        in accordance with everything that He promised. Not one word has failed of
        all His good promise, which He spoke through Moses His servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'May the Lord our God be with us as He was with our fathers; may He
        not leave us nor abandon us [to our enemies], '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'that He may guide our hearts to Himself, to walk in all His ways
        [following Him] and to keep His commandments, His statutes, and His precepts
        which He commanded our fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Let these words of mine, with which I have made supplication before
        the Lord, be near to the Lord our God day and night, so that He will maintain
        the cause and right of His servant and of His people Israel as each day requires, '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'so that all the peoples of the earth may know that the Lord is God;
        there is no one else. '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: Dedicatory Sacrifices'
      title: Dedicatory Sacrifices
      number: 61
      content: "Therefore, your hearts are to be wholly devoted to the Lord our God,
        to walk in His statutes and to keep His commandments, as [you are doing]
        today.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'Then the king and all [the people of] Israel with him [repeatedly]
        offered sacrifice before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'Solomon offered as peace offerings to the Lord: 22,000 oxen and 120,000
        sheep. So the king and all the Israelites dedicated the house (temple) of
        the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'On that same day the king consecrated the middle of the courtyard
        that was in front of the house (temple) of the Lord; for he offered there
        the burnt offerings, the grain offerings, and the fat of the peace offerings,
        because the bronze altar that was before the Lord was too small to hold [all]
        the burnt offerings, the grain offerings and the fat of the peace offerings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: "So at that time Solomon held the feast, and all Israel with him,
        a great assembly, from the entrance of Hamath [on the northern border of
        Israel] to the Brook of Egypt [at Israel\u2019s southern border], before
        the Lord our God, for seven days and seven more days [beyond the prescribed
        period for the Feast of Booths], fourteen days in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: On the eighth (fifteenth) day he sent the people away and they blessed
        the king. Then they went to their tents joyful and in good spirits because
        of all the goodness which the Lord had shown to David His servant and Israel
        His people.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Promise and Warning"
      title: "God\u2019s Promise and Warning"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now it happened when Solomon had finished building the house (temple)
        of the Lord and the king\u2019s house (palace), and all else which he was
        pleased to do, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that the Lord appeared to Solomon a second time, just as He had appeared
        to him at Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The Lord told him, \u201CI have heard your prayer and supplication
        which you have made before Me; I have consecrated this house which you have
        built by putting My Name and My Presence there forever. My eyes and My heart
        shall be there perpetually. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As for you, if you walk (live your life) before Me, as David your
        father walked, in integrity of heart and in uprightness, acting in accordance
        with everything that I have commanded you, and will keep My statutes and
        My precepts, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "then I will establish the throne of your kingdom over Israel forever,
        just as I promised your father David, saying, \u2018You shall not be without
        a man (descendant) on the throne of Israel.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CBut if you or your sons turn away from following Me, and do
        not keep My commandments and My statutes which I have set before you, but
        go and serve other gods and worship them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'then I will cut off Israel from the land which I have given them,
        and I will cast out of My sight the house which I have consecrated for My
        Name and Presence. Then Israel will become a proverb (a saying) and a byword
        (object of ridicule) among all the peoples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "This house (temple) will become a heap of ruins; everyone who passes
        by will be appalled and sneer and say, \u2018Why has the Lord done such a
        thing to this land and to this house?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Cities Given to Hiram'
      title: Cities Given to Hiram
      number: 9
      content: "And they [who know] will say, \u2018Because they abandoned the Lord
        their God, who brought their fathers out of the land of Egypt, and they have
        chosen other gods and have worshiped and served them; that is the reason
        the Lord has brought on them all this adversity.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now at the end of twenty years, in which Solomon had built the two
        houses, the temple of the Lord and the palace of the king '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '(Hiram king of Tyre had supplied Solomon with as much cedar and cypress
        timber [from Lebanon] and gold as he desired), at that time King Solomon
        gave Hiram twenty cities in the land of Galilee (northern Israel). '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Hiram came from Tyre to see the cities which Solomon had given
        him, and they did not please him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He said, \u201CWhat are these cities [good for] which you have given
        me, my brother?\u201D So they have been called the land of Cabul (like nothing,
        unproductive) to this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Hiram sent to the king 120 talents of gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now this is the account of the forced labor which King Solomon conscripted
        to build the house of the Lord, his own house, the Millo (fortification),
        the wall of Jerusalem, [and the fortress cities of] Hazor, Megiddo, and Gezer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For Pharaoh king of Egypt had gone up and taken Gezer, burned it
        with fire and killed the Canaanites who lived in the city, and he had given
        it as a dowry to his daughter, Solomon\u2019s wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So Solomon rebuilt [and fortified] Gezer and Lower Beth-horon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Baalath and Tamar in the wilderness, in the land of Judah,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and all the storage cities [for surplus provisions] which Solomon
        had, and the cities for his chariots and cities for his horsemen, and whatever
        it pleased Solomon to build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon, and in all the land
        under his rule. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'As for all the people who were left of the Amorites, Hittites, Perizzites,
        Hivites, and Jebusites, who were not of the sons (descendants) of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'their children who were left after them in the land, whom the Israelites
        were unable to completely destroy, from them Solomon levied (conscripted)
        forced laborers, even to this day (the date of this writing). '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But Solomon did not make slaves of the sons of Israel; for they were
        men of war (soldiers), his servants, his officers, his captains, his chariot
        commanders, and his horsemen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "These were the chief officers who were over Solomon\u2019s work,
        five hundred and fifty, who ruled over the people doing the work.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "As soon as Pharaoh\u2019s daughter came up from the City of David
        to her house which Solomon had built for her, then he built the Millo (fortification).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Three times a year [during the major annual festivals] Solomon offered
        burnt offerings and peace offerings on the altar he had built to the Lord,
        and he burned incense with them before the Lord. So he finished the house
        [of the Lord].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'King Solomon built a fleet of ships in Ezion-geber, which is near
        Eloth on the shore of the Red Sea (Sea of Reeds), in the land of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Hiram [king of Tyre] sent his servants with the fleet, sailors
        who knew the sea, along with the servants of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: They came to Ophir and took four hundred and twenty talents of gold
        from there, and brought it to King Solomon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Queen of Sheba'
      title: The Queen of Sheba
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon concerning
        the name of the Lord, she came to test him with riddles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So she came to Jerusalem with a very large caravan (entourage), with
        camels carrying spices, a great quantity of gold, and precious stones. When
        she came to Solomon, she spoke with him about everything that was on her
        mind [to discover the extent of his wisdom]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Solomon answered all her questions; there was nothing hidden from
        the king which he did not explain to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When the queen of Sheba had seen all the wisdom of Solomon, and the
        house (palace) which he had built, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'the food on his table, the seating of his servants (court officials),
        the attendance of his waiters and their attire, his cupbearers, his stairway
        by which he went up to the house (temple) of the Lord, she was breathless
        and awed [by the wonder of it all]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then she told the king, \u201CThe report which I heard in my own
        land about your words and wisdom is true! "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I did not believe the report until I came and saw it with my own
        eyes. Behold, the half of it was not told to me. You exceed in wisdom and
        prosperity the report which I heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'How blessed (fortunate, happy) are your men! How blessed are these
        your servants who stand continually before you, hearing your wisdom! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Blessed be the Lord your God who delighted in you to set you on the
        throne of Israel! Because the Lord loved Israel forever, He made you king
        to execute justice and righteousness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'She gave the king a hundred and twenty talents of gold and a very
        great quantity of spices and precious stones. Never again did such an abundance
        of spices come in [to Israel] as that which the queen of Sheba gave King
        Solomon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Also the ships of Hiram, which brought gold from Ophir, brought in
        from Ophir a great quantity of almug wood (sandalwood) and precious stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "From the almug wood (sandalwood) the king made pillars for the house
        of the Lord and for the king\u2019s palace, and also lyres and harps for
        the singers. Such almug wood did not come in [to Israel] again, nor has it
        been seen to this day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Wealth, Splendor and Wisdom'
      title: Wealth, Splendor and Wisdom
      number: 13
      content: 'King Solomon [in turn] gave to the queen of Sheba everything that
        she wanted, whatever she asked, besides what he gave to her from his royal
        bounty. So she returned to her own country, she and her servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now the weight of the gold that came to Solomon in one [particular]
        year was six hundred and sixty-six talents of gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'besides the taxes from the traders and from the wares of the merchants,
        and [the tribute money] from all the kings of the Arabs (Bedouins) and the
        governors of the country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'King Solomon made two hundred large shields of beaten (hammered)
        gold; six hundred shekels of gold went into each shield. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He made three hundred smaller shields of beaten gold; three minas
        of gold went into each shield. The king put them in the House of the Forest
        of Lebanon [the king\u2019s armory]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Also the king made a great throne of ivory and overlaid it with the
        finest gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The throne had six steps, and a round top was attached to the throne
        from the back. On either side of the seat were armrests, and two lions stood
        beside the armrests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Twelve lions stood there, one on either end of each of the six steps;
        there was nothing like it made for any other kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "All King Solomon\u2019s drinking vessels were of gold, and all vessels
        of the House of the Forest of Lebanon were of pure gold. None were of silver;
        it was not considered valuable in the days of Solomon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For the king had at sea the [large cargo] ships of Tarshish with
        the ships of Hiram. Once every three years the ships of Tarshish came bringing
        gold, silver, ivory, monkeys, and peacocks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So King Solomon exceeded all the kings of the earth in wealth and
        in wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'All the earth was seeking the presence of Solomon, to hear his wisdom
        which God had put in his mind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Every man brought a gift [of tribute]: articles of silver and gold,
        garments, weapons, spices, horses, and mules, so much year by year.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now Solomon collected chariots and horsemen; he had 1,400 chariots
        and 12,000 horsemen, which he stationed in the chariot cities and with the
        king in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The king made silver as common in Jerusalem as stones, and cedars
        as plentiful as the sycamore trees that are in the lowland. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Solomon\u2019s horses were imported from Egypt and from Kue, and
        the king\u2019s merchants acquired them from Kue, for a price. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "A chariot could be imported from Egypt for six hundred shekels of
        silver, and a horse for a hundred and fifty; and in the same way they exported
        them, by the king\u2019s merchants, to all the kings of the Hittites and
        to the kings of Aram (Syria)."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Turns from God'
      title: Solomon Turns from God
      number: 1
      content: '  Now king Solomon [defiantly] loved many foreign women along with
        the daughter of Pharaoh: Moabite, Ammonite, Edomite, Sidonian, and Hittite
        women, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "from the very nations of whom the Lord said to the Israelites, \u201CYou
        shall not associate with them, nor shall they associate with you, for the
        result will be that they will turn away your hearts to follow their gods.\u201D
        Yet Solomon clung to these in love. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He had seven hundred wives, princesses, and three hundred concubines,
        and his wives turned his heart away [from God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For when Solomon was old, his wives turned his heart away after other
        gods; and his heart was not completely devoted to the Lord his God, as was
        the heart of his father David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For Solomon went after Ashtoreth, the [fertility] goddess of the
        Sidonians, and after Milcom the horror (detestable idol) of the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Solomon did evil [things] in the sight of the Lord, and did not follow
        the Lord fully, as his father David had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Solomon built a high place for [worshiping] Chemosh the horror
        (detestable idol) of Moab, on the hill which is east of Jerusalem, and for
        Molech the horror (detestable idol) of the sons of Ammon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he did the same for all of his foreign wives, who burned incense
        and sacrificed to their gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the Lord became angry with Solomon because his heart was turned
        away from the Lord, the God of Israel, who had appeared to him twice, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and had commanded him concerning this thing, that he should not follow
        other gods; but he did not observe (remember, obey) what the Lord had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore the Lord said to Solomon, \u201CBecause you have done this
        and have not kept My covenant and My statutes, which I have commanded you,
        I will certainly tear the kingdom away from you and give it to your servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'However, I will not do it in your lifetime, for the sake of your
        father David, but I will tear it out of the hand of your son (Rehoboam). '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: God Raises Adversaries'
      title: God Raises Adversaries
      number: 13
      content: "However, I will not tear away all the kingdom; I will give one tribe
        (Judah) to your son for the sake of My servant David and for the sake of
        Jerusalem which I have chosen.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the Lord stirred up an adversary against Solomon, Hadad the
        Edomite; he was of royal descent in Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For it came about, when David was in Edom, and Joab the commander
        of the army had gone up to bury those killed [in battle] and had struck down
        every male in Edom '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '(for Joab and all [the army of] Israel stayed there six months, until
        he had killed every male in Edom), '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "that Hadad escaped to Egypt, he and some Edomites from his father\u2019s
        servants with him, while Hadad was [still] a little boy. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They set out from Midian [south of Edom] and came to Paran, and took
        men with them from Paran and came to Egypt, to Pharaoh king of Egypt, who
        gave [young] Hadad a house and ordered food and provisions for him and gave
        him land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hadad found great favor with Pharaoh, so that he gave Hadad in marriage
        the sister of his own wife, the sister of Tahpenes the queen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The sister of Tahpenes gave birth to Genubath, Hadad\u2019s son,
        whom Tahpenes weaned in Pharaoh\u2019s house; and Genubath was in Pharaoh\u2019s
        household among the sons of Pharaoh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But when Hadad heard in Egypt that David had died and that Joab the
        commander of the army was dead, Hadad said to Pharaoh, \u201CLet me leave,
        so that I may go to my own country.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to him, \u201CBut what have you lacked with me
        that now you ask to go to your own country?\u201D He replied, \u201CNothing;
        nevertheless you must let me go.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'God also stirred up another adversary for Solomon, Rezon the son
        of Eliada, who had fled from his master, Hadadezer king of Zobah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Rezon gathered men to himself and became leader of a marauding band,
        after David killed those in Zobah. They went to Damascus and stayed there
        and they reigned in Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So Rezon was an adversary to Israel all the days of Solomon, along
        with the evil that Hadad inflicted. Rezon hated Israel and reigned over Aram
        (Syria).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jeroboam, Solomon\u2019s servant, the son of Nebat, an Ephrathite
        of Zeredah whose mother\u2019s name was Zeruah, a widow, also rebelled against
        the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now this is the reason why he rebelled against the king: Solomon
        built the Millo (fortification) and he repaired and closed the breach of
        the city of his father David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The man Jeroboam was a brave warrior and when Solomon saw that the
        young man was industrious, he put him in charge of all the forced labor of
        the house of Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'It came about at that time, when Jeroboam left Jerusalem, that the
        prophet Ahijah the Shilonite met him on the road. Now Ahijah had covered
        himself with a new cloak; and the two of them were alone in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Ahijah took hold of the new cloak which he was wearing and tore
        it into twelve pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "He said to Jeroboam, \u201CTake ten pieces for yourself; for thus
        says the Lord, the God of Israel, \u2018Behold, I am going to tear the kingdom
        from the hand of Solomon and give you ten tribes\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "but he [and his descendants] shall have one tribe (Benjamin was annexed
        to Judah), for the sake of My servant David and for the sake of Jerusalem,
        the city which I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'because they have abandoned Me and have worshiped Ashtoreth the goddess
        of the Sidonians, Chemosh the god of the Moabites, and Milcom the god of
        the sons of Ammon; and they have not walked in My ways and followed My commandments,
        doing what is right in My sight and keeping My statutes and My ordinances
        as did his father David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'However, I will not take the entire kingdom out of his hand; but
        I will make him ruler all the days of his life for the sake of My servant
        David, whom I chose because he kept My commandments and My statutes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "But I will take the kingdom out of his son\u2019s hand and give it
        to you: ten tribes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Yet to his son I will give one tribe, so that My servant David may
        have a lamp always before Me in Jerusalem, the city where I have chosen to
        put My Name and Presence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'I will take you [Jeroboam], and you shall reign over whatever your
        soul desires; and you shall be king over Israel (the ten northern tribes). '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then it shall be, that if you listen to all that I command you and
        walk in My ways, and do what is right in My sight, keeping and observing
        My statutes and My commandments, as My servant David did, then I will be
        with you and build you an enduring house, as I built for David, and I will
        give Israel to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And in this way I will afflict the descendants of David for this
        (their sin), but not forever.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: The Death of Solomon'
      title: The Death of Solomon
      number: 40
      content: 'So Solomon attempted to kill Jeroboam; but Jeroboam set out and escaped
        to Egypt, to Shishak king of Egypt, and stayed in Egypt until Solomon died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "The rest of the acts of Solomon\u2014and all that he did, and his
        wisdom\u2014are they not written in the book of the acts of Solomon? "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The time Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel was forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: And Solomon slept [in death] with his fathers and was buried in the
        city of his father David. Rehoboam his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: King Rehoboam Acts Foolishly'
      title: King Rehoboam Acts Foolishly
      number: 1
      content: '  Rehoboam went to Shechem, for all Israel had come to Shechem to
        make him king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now when Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard about it, he was living
        in Egypt (for he was still in Egypt, where he had fled from King Solomon). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So they sent word and called for him, and Jeroboam and all the assembly
        of Israel came and spoke to Rehoboam, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYour father made our yoke (burden) heavy; so now lighten the
        hard labor and the heavy yoke your father imposed on us, and we will serve
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Rehoboam replied to them, \u201CLeave for three days, then come back
        to me [for my decision].\u201D So the people left.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "King Rehoboam consulted with the elders who had served and advised
        his father Solomon while he was still alive and said, \u201CHow do you advise
        me to answer this people?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They spoke to him, saying, \u201CIf you will be a servant to this
        people today, and will serve them and grant their request, and speak good
        words to them, then they will be your servants forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But he ignored the advice which the elders gave him and consulted
        the young men who grew up with him and served him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He said to them, \u201CWhat do you advise that we answer this people
        who have said to me, \u2018Lighten the yoke (burden) which your father put
        on us\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The young men who had grown up with him answered, \u201CThis is what
        you should say to this people who told you, \u2018Your father made our yoke
        heavy, but as for you, make our yoke lighter\u2019\u2014say this to them:
        \u2018My little finger is thicker than my father\u2019s loins [and my reign
        will be even more severe]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And now, whereas my father loaded you with a heavy yoke, I will add
        to your yoke. My father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline
        you with scorpions.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Jeroboam and all the people came back to Rehoboam on the third day,
        just as the king had instructed, saying, \u201CReturn to me on the third
        day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The king answered the people harshly and ignored the advice which
        the elders had given him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and spoke to them in accordance with the advice of the young men,
        saying, \u201CMy father made your yoke heavy, but as for me, I will add to
        your yoke; my father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you
        with scorpions.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Kingdom Divided; Jeroboam Rules Israel'
      title: The Kingdom Divided; Jeroboam Rules Israel
      number: 15
      content: 'So the king did not listen to the people; for the situation was from
        the Lord, so that He might fulfill His word which He spoke through Ahijah
        the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So when all [the ten northern tribes of] Israel saw that the king
        did not listen to them, the people replied to the king, saying,\u201CWhat
        portion do we have in David?  We have no inheritance in the son of Jesse;To
        your tents, O Israel!Look now after your own house, David!\u201DThen Israel
        went back to their tents. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But as for the sons (descendants) of Israel who lived in the cities
        of Judah [including Benjamin], Rehoboam reigned over them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then King Rehoboam sent Adoram, who was in charge of the forced labor
        [to represent him], and all Israel stoned him to death. And King Rehoboam
        quickly mounted his chariot to escape to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Israel (the ten northern tribes) has rebelled against the house
        (royal line) of David to this day (the date of this writing).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'It came about when all Israel heard that Jeroboam had returned, that
        they sent word and called him to the assembly and made him king over all
        Israel. None followed the house of David except the tribe of Judah [including
        Benjamin].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now when Rehoboam arrived in Jerusalem, he assembled all the [fighting
        men from the] house of Judah, with the tribe of Benjamin, 180,000 chosen
        warriors, to fight against the house of Israel to bring the kingdom back
        to Rehoboam the son of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But the word of God came to Shemaiah the man of God, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CTell Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and all the
        house (fighting men) of Judah and Benjamin and the rest of the people, "
      comments: []
    - name: "24: Jeroboam\u2019s Idolatry"
      title: "Jeroboam\u2019s Idolatry"
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord, \u201CYou shall not go up and fight against
        your brothers, the sons of Israel. Let every man return to his house, for
        this thing has come about from Me.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D So they
        listened to the word of the Lord and returned to go home, in accordance with
        the word of the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Jeroboam built Shechem [as his royal city] in the hill country
        of Ephraim and lived there. He went out from there and rebuilt Penuel [as
        a stronghold]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jeroboam [doubted God\u2019s promise to him and] said in his heart,
        \u201CNow the kingdom will return to the house of David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "If these people go up to the house of the Lord in Jerusalem to offer
        sacrifices, then their heart will turn to their lord, to Rehoboam king of
        Judah; and they will kill me and return to Rehoboam king of Judah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So the king took counsel [and followed bad advice] and made two calves
        of gold. And he said to the people, \u201CIt is too much for you to go [all
        the way] up to Jerusalem; behold your gods, O Israel, who brought you up
        out of the land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He set the one [golden calf] in Bethel, and the other he put in Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now this thing became a sin [for Israel]; because the people went
        to worship before the one [or the other of them] as far as Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And Jeroboam also made houses on high places, and he made priests
        from all people who were not of the sons (descendants) of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Jeroboam held a feast on the fifteenth day of the eighth month, like
        the feast which is kept in Judah, and he went up to the altar; he did this
        in Bethel, sacrificing to the calves which he had made. And he stationed
        in Bethel the priests of the high places which he had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So he went up to the altar which he had made in Bethel on the fifteenth
        day of the eighth month, in the month which he had devised in his own heart
        [in defiance of God\u2019s commandments]; and he held a feast for the Israelites
        and he went up to the altar to burn incense [in defiance of God\u2019s law.]"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jeroboam Warned, Stricken'
      title: Jeroboam Warned, Stricken
      number: 1
      content: '  Now behold, there came a man of God from Judah to Bethel by the
        word (command) of the Lord, while Jeroboam was standing by the altar [which
        he had built] to burn incense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The man cried out against the [idolatrous] altar by the word of the
        Lord, \u201CO altar, altar, thus says the Lord: \u2018Behold, a son shall
        be born to the house of David, Josiah by name; and on you shall he sacrifice
        [the bodies of] the priests of the high places who burn incense on you, and
        human bones shall be burned on you.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And he gave a sign the same day, saying, \u201CThis is the sign which
        the Lord has spoken: \u2018Behold, the altar shall be split apart and the
        ashes that are on it shall be poured out.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When the king heard the words which the man of God cried out against
        the altar in Bethel, Jeroboam put out his hand from the altar, saying, \u201CSeize
        him!\u201D And his hand which he had put out against him withered, so that
        he was unable to pull it back to himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The altar also was split apart and the ashes were poured out from
        the altar in accordance with the sign which the man of God had given by the
        word of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The king answered and said to the man of God, \u201CPlease entreat
        [the favor of] the Lord your God and pray for me, that my hand may be restored
        to me.\u201D So the man of God entreated the Lord, and the king\u2019s hand
        was restored to him and became as it was before. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the king said to the man of God, \u201CCome home with me and
        refresh yourself, and I will give you a reward.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But the man of God said to the king, \u201CEven if you were to give
        me half your house (wealth), I would not go with you, nor would I eat bread
        or drink water in this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For I was commanded by the word of the Lord, \u2018You shall not
        eat bread or drink water, nor shall you return by the way you came.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Disobedient Prophet'
      title: The Disobedient Prophet
      number: 10
      content: 'So he went another way and did not return by the way that he came
        to Bethel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now there was an old prophet living in Bethel; and his sons came
        and told him everything that the man of God had done that day in Bethel;
        they also told their father the words which he had spoken to the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Their father asked them, \u201CWhich way did he go?\u201D For his
        sons had seen which way the man of God who came from Judah had gone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He said to his sons, \u201CSaddle the donkey for me.\u201D So they
        saddled the donkey for him and he rode away on it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and he went after the man of God. And he found him sitting under
        an oak (terebinth) tree, and he said to him, \u201CAre you the man of God
        who came from Judah?\u201D And he said, \u201CI am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then he said to him, \u201CCome home with me and eat bread.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He said, \u201CI cannot return with you nor go in with you, nor will
        I eat bread or drink water with you in this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For I was told by the word of the Lord, \u2018You shall not eat bread
        nor drink water there, nor shall you return by going the way that you came.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He answered him, \u201CI too am a prophet, as you are; and an angel
        spoke to me by the word of the Lord, saying, \u2018Bring him back with you
        to your house, so that he may eat bread and drink water.\u2019\u2009\u201D
        But he lied to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So the man of God went back with him, and ate bread in his house
        and drank water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now it happened as they were sitting at the table, that the word
        of the Lord came to the prophet who had brought him back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he cried out to the man of God who had come from Judah, \u201CThus
        says the Lord, \u2018Because you have disobeyed the word of the Lord and
        have not kept the commandment which the Lord your God commanded you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "but have come back and have eaten bread and drunk water in the place
        of which the Lord said to you, \u201CYou shall not eat bread nor drink water\u201D;
        your body shall not come to the tomb of your fathers (ancestors).\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'After the prophet of the house had eaten bread and after he had drunk,
        he saddled the donkey for the prophet whom he had brought back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now when he had gone, a lion met him by the road and killed him,
        and his body was thrown in the road, with the donkey standing beside it;
        the lion was also standing beside the body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And there were men passing by, and they saw the body thrown in the
        road, and the lion standing beside the body. So they came and told about
        it in the city [of Bethel] where the old prophet lived.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When the prophet who had brought him back from the road heard about
        it, he said, \u201CIt is the man of God who was disobedient to the word of
        the Lord; therefore the Lord has given him to the lion, which has torn him
        and killed him, in accordance with the word of the Lord which He spoke to
        him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he said to his sons, \u201CSaddle the donkey for me.\u201D And
        they saddled it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he went and found the body thrown on the road, and the donkey
        and the lion standing beside the body; the lion [miraculously] had not eaten
        the body or attacked the donkey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then the prophet picked up the body of the man of God and laid it
        on the donkey and brought it back, and he came into the city (Bethel) of
        the old prophet to mourn and to bury him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And he laid the body in his own grave, and they mourned over him,
        saying, \u201CAlas, my brother!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then after he had buried him, he said to his sons, \u201CWhen I am
        dead, bury me in the grave in which the man of God is buried; lay my bones
        beside his bones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "For the words which he cried out by the word of the Lord against
        the altar in Bethel and against all the houses of the high places which are
        in the cities of Samaria shall certainly come to pass.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'After this event, Jeroboam [still] did not turn from his evil way,
        but again made priests for the high places from among all the people. He
        ordained anyone who was willing, so that there would be priests for the high
        places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And this thing (idol worship) became the sin of the house of Jeroboam
        to blot it out and eliminate it from the face of the earth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ahijah Prophesies against the King'
      title: Ahijah Prophesies against the King
      number: 1
      content: '  At that time Abijah the son [and crown prince, heir] of Jeroboam
        became sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Jeroboam said to his wife, \u201CPlease get up and disguise yourself,
        so that people will not know that you are Jeroboam\u2019s wife, and go to
        Shiloh. Ahijah the prophet is there, the one who told me that I would be
        king over this people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Take with you ten loaves of bread, some cakes, and a bottle of honey,
        and go to him. He will tell you what will happen to the boy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jeroboam\u2019s wife did so. She got up and went [twenty miles] to
        Shiloh, and came to the house of Ahijah. Now Ahijah could not see, because
        his eyes were dim from old age. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the Lord said to Ahijah, \u201CBehold, the wife of Jeroboam is
        coming to inquire of you about her son, because he is sick. You shall say
        such and such to her, for when she arrives, she will pretend to be another
        woman.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So when Ahijah heard the sound of her feet as she came in the doorway,
        he said, \u201CCome in, wife of Jeroboam. Why do you pretend to be another
        woman? For I have been sent to you [by God] with a harsh message. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Go, tell Jeroboam, \u2018This is what the Lord, the God of Israel,
        says: \u201CBecause I exalted you from among the people and made you leader
        over My people Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and tore the kingdom away from the house of David and gave it to
        you\u2014but you have not been like My servant David, who kept My commandments
        and followed Me with all his heart, to do only what was right in My eyes, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "but have done more evil than all [the kings] who were before you;
        for you have gone and made for yourself other gods and molten images to provoke
        Me to anger, and have cast Me behind your back\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'therefore behold, I am bringing evil on the house (royal line) of
        Jeroboam, and I will cut off (destroy) from Jeroboam every male, both bond
        and free, in Israel, and will utterly sweep away the house of Jeroboam as
        one sweeps away dung until it is all gone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The dogs will eat [the carcass of] anyone belonging to Jeroboam who
        dies in the city, and the birds of the sky will eat [the carcass of] anyone
        who dies in the field, for the Lord has spoken it.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now as for you (Jeroboam\u2019s wife), arise, go to your own house.
        When your feet enter the city, the child [Abijah] will die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "All Israel shall mourn for him and bury him, for he alone of Jeroboam\u2019s
        family  will come to [be placed in] the grave, because in him there was found
        something good and pleasing toward the Lord, the God of Israel, in the house
        of Jeroboam. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Moreover, the Lord will raise up for Himself a king over Israel who
        will cut off the house (royal line) of Jeroboam this day and from now on.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThe Lord will strike Israel, as a reed is shaken in the water;
        and He will uproot Israel from this good land which He gave to their fathers,
        and He will scatter them beyond the [Euphrates] River, because they have
        made their Asherim, provoking the Lord to anger. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He will give up Israel because of the sins of Jeroboam which he has
        committed, and with which he has made Israel sin [by leading them into idolatry].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Jeroboam\u2019s wife arose and left and came to Tirzah [the king\u2019s
        residence]. As she was entering the threshold of the house, the child [Abijah]
        died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And all Israel buried him and mourned for him, in accordance with
        the word of the Lord which He spoke through His servant Ahijah the prophet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now as for the rest of the acts of Jeroboam, how he made war and
        how he reigned, behold, they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of
        the Kings of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Rehoboam Misleads Judah'
      title: Rehoboam Misleads Judah
      number: 20
      content: 'The time that Jeroboam reigned was twenty-two years, and he slept
        with his fathers [in death]; and Nadab his son reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now Rehoboam the son of Solomon reigned in Judah. Rehoboam was forty-one
        years old when he became king, and he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem,
        the city the Lord had chosen from all the tribes of Israel in which to put
        His Name (Presence). His mother\u2019s name was Naamah the Ammonitess. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And [the people of] Judah did evil in the sight of the Lord. They
        provoked Him to jealousy more than all that their fathers had done, with
        their sins which they had committed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For they also built for themselves high places [to worship idols]
        and sacred pillars and Asherim [for the goddess Asherah]. These were on every
        high hill and under every luxuriant tree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'There were also male cult prostitutes in the land. They committed
        all the repulsive acts of the nations which the Lord dispossessed before
        the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now in the fifth year of King Rehoboam, Shishak king of Egypt [Jeroboam\u2019s
        brother-in-law] came up against Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "He took away the treasures of the house (temple) of the Lord and
        the treasures of the king\u2019s house; he took away everything, he even
        took all the shields of gold which Solomon had made. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "So King Rehoboam made bronze shields to replace them and handed them
        over to the captains of the palace guard who guarded the doorway of the king\u2019s
        house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And as often as the king went into the house of the Lord, the guards
        would carry them and bring them back into the guardroom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now as for the rest of the acts of Rehoboam, and everything that
        he did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of
        Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'There was also war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam continually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And Rehoboam slept with his fathers [in death] and was buried with
        his fathers in the City of David. His mother\u2019s name was Naamah the Ammonitess.
        Abijam (Abijah) his son became king in his place."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abijam Reigns over Judah'
      title: Abijam Reigns over Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  In the eighteenth year of King Jeroboam the son of Nebat, Abijam
        became king over Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He reigned three years in Jerusalem. His mother was Maacah [grand]daughter
        of Abishalom (Absalom). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He walked in all the sins [of idol worship] that his father [Rehoboam]
        committed before him; and his heart was not entirely devoted to the Lord
        his God, like the heart of his father (forefather) David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Nevertheless, for David\u2019s sake the Lord his God gave him a lamp
        (descendant on the throne) in Jerusalem, setting up his son after him and
        establishing Jerusalem, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'because David did what was right in the eyes of the Lord, and had
        not turned aside from anything that He commanded him all the days of his
        life, except in the matter of [the betrayal of] Uriah the Hittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "There was war between Rehoboam [Abijam\u2019s father] and Jeroboam
        all the days of Rehoboam\u2019s life.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Asa Succeeds Abijam'
      title: Asa Succeeds Abijam
      number: 7
      content: 'Now as for the rest of the acts of Abijam and everything that he
        did, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah?
        And there was war between Abijam and Jeroboam.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Abijam slept with his fathers [in death] and they buried him in the
        City of David. Asa his son became king in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So in the twentieth year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Asa began to
        reign as king over Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He reigned forty-one years in Jerusalem. His [great-grand]mother
        was Maacah the daughter of Abishalom (Absalom). '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Asa did what was right in the eyes of the Lord, as did his father
        (forefather) David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He expelled the male cult prostitutes (sodomites) from the land and
        removed all the idols that his fathers [Solomon, Rehoboam, and Abijam] had
        made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He also deposed his [great-grand]mother Maacah from being queen mother,
        because she had made a horrid (obscene, vulgar) image for [the goddess] Asherah.
        Asa cut down her horrid image, and burned it by the Brook Kidron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But the high places [of idol worship] were not removed. Nevertheless,
        Asa\u2019s heart was entirely devoted to the Lord all his days. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He brought the things which his father had dedicated and the things
        which he had dedicated into the house of the Lord\u2014silver, gold, and
        utensils and accessories.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their
        days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Baasha king of Israel went up against Judah and fortified Ramah [north
        of Jerusalem], in order to prevent anyone from going out or coming in to
        Asa king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Asa took all the silver and gold left in the treasuries of the
        house of the Lord and the treasuries of the palace of the king and handed
        them over to his servants. And King Asa sent them to Ben-hadad the son of
        Tabrimmon, the son of Hezion, king of Aram (Syria), who lived in Damascus,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CLet there be a treaty between me and you, as there was between
        my father and your father. Behold, I have sent you a gift of silver and gold;
        go, break your treaty with Baasha king of Israel, so that he will withdraw
        from me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Ben-hadad listened to king Asa and sent the commanders of his
        armies against the cities of Israel, and conquered Ijon, Dan, Abel-beth-maacah,
        and all Chinneroth [the region of the Sea of Galilee], along with all the
        land of Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When Baasha heard about it, he stopped fortifying Ramah and stayed
        in Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Jehoshaphat Succeeds Asa'
      title: Jehoshaphat Succeeds Asa
      number: 22
      content: "Then King Asa made a proclamation to all Judah\u2014none was exempt\u2014and
        they carried away the stones of Ramah and its timber with which Baasha had
        built [the fortifications]. And King Asa built with them [border fortresses
        at] Geba of Benjamin and Mizpah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now as for the rest of all the acts of Asa, all his might, everything
        that he did, and the cities which he built, are they not written in the Book
        of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? But during the time of his old age
        he had a foot disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Nadab, then Baasha, Rules over Israel'
      title: Nadab, then Baasha, Rules over Israel
      number: 24
      content: 'Asa slept with his fathers [in death] and was buried with his fathers
        in the city of his father David. Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now Nadab the son of Jeroboam began to reign over Israel in the second
        year of Asa king of Judah, and he reigned over Israel for two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord and walked in the way of his
        father [Jeroboam] and in his sin [of idolatry], with which he made Israel
        sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Baasha the son of Ahijah of the house (tribe) of Issachar conspired
        against Nadab, and Baasha struck him down at Gibbethon, which belonged to
        the Philistines, while Nadab and all Israel were laying siege to Gibbethon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Baasha killed Nadab in the third year of Asa king of Judah, and
        reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "As soon as he was king, Baasha struck down all the household of Jeroboam.
        He did not leave for Jeroboam anyone alive, but he destroyed them in accordance
        with the word of the Lord which He had spoken through His servant Ahijah
        the Shilonite\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'because of the sins committed by Jeroboam and which he made Israel
        commit, and because he provoked the Lord God of Israel to anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: War with Judah'
      title: War with Judah
      number: 31
      content: "Now as for the rest of Nadab\u2019s acts and everything that he did,
        are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'There was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'In the third year of Asa king of Judah, Baasha the son of Ahijah
        became king over all Israel in Tirzah [the capital city], and reigned twenty-four
        years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: He did evil in the sight of the Lord and walked in the way of Jeroboam
        and in his sin [of idolatry] with which he made Israel sin.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prophecy against Baasha'
      title: Prophecy against Baasha
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the word of the Lord came to Jehu the son of Hanani against
        Baasha, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CBecause I exalted you [Baasha] from the dust and made you leader
        over My people Israel, and you walked in the way of Jeroboam and made My
        people Israel sin, provoking Me to anger with their sins [of idol worship], "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'behold, I am going to sweep away Baasha and his household (family),
        and I will make your house (royal line) like that of Jeroboam the son of
        Nebat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The dogs will eat anyone belonging to Baasha who dies in the city,
        and the birds of the sky will eat anyone belonging to him who dies in the
        field.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Israelite Kings'
      title: The Israelite Kings
      number: 5
      content: 'Now as for the rest of the acts of Baasha, what he did and his might,
        are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Baasha slept with his fathers [in death] and was buried in Tirzah.
        Elah his son became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Moreover, the word of the Lord came against Baasha and his household
        through the prophet Jehu the son of Hanani, both for all the evil that Baasha
        did in the sight of the Lord in provoking Him to anger with the work of his
        hands (idolatry), in being like the house of Jeroboam, and because he [willingly]
        destroyed it (the family of Jeroboam).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the twenty-sixth year of Asa king of Judah, Elah the son of Baasha
        became king over Israel in Tirzah, and reigned two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "His servant Zimri, commander of half his chariots, conspired against
        Elah. Now Elah was in Tirzah, getting drunk in the house of Arza, who was
        in charge of the [king\u2019s] household in Tirzah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Zimri came in and struck and killed Elah in the twenty-seventh
        year of Asa king of Judah, and became king in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When he became king, as soon as he sat on his throne, he killed the
        entire household of Baasha; he did not leave a single male [alive], either
        of his relatives or his friends.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Thus Zimri destroyed the entire household of Baasha, in accordance
        with the word of the Lord which He spoke against Baasha through Jehu the
        prophet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'for all the sins of Baasha and the sins of Elah his son, which they
        committed, and made Israel commit, provoking the Lord God of Israel to anger
        with their idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now as for the rest of the acts of Elah and everything that he did,
        are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, Zimri reigned [over
        Israel] for seven days at Tirzah. Now the troops were camped against Gibbethon,
        [a city] which belonged to the Philistines, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and the people who were camped heard it said, \u201CZimri has conspired
        and has also struck down the king.\u201D So all Israel made Omri, the commander
        of the army, king over Israel that day in the camp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Omri went up from Gibbethon, and all Israel with him, and they
        besieged Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When Zimri saw that the city was taken, he went into the fortress
        of the king\u2019s palace; and while inside, he set fire to the king\u2019s
        palace and died, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'because of the sins he had committed, doing evil in the sight of
        the Lord, by walking in the way of Jeroboam, and because of his sin he caused
        Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now as for the rest of the acts of Zimri, and his [treasonous] conspiracy
        which he committed, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of
        the Kings of Israel?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the people of Israel were divided in half. Half of the people
        followed Tibni the son of Ginath, to make him king, and the other half followed
        Omri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But the people who followed Omri prevailed over the people who followed
        Tibni the son of Ginath. So Tibni died and Omri became king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In the thirty-first year of Asa king of Judah, Omri became king over
        Israel and reigned for twelve years. He reigned six years at Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Omri bought the hill Samaria from Shemer for two talents of silver,
        and he built a city on the hill [and fortified it], and named the city which
        he built Samaria, after the owner of the hill, Shemer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But Omri did evil in the sight of the Lord, and acted more wickedly
        than all who came before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He walked in all the ways of Jeroboam the son of Nebat and in his
        sin, which he made Israel commit, provoking the Lord God of Israel, [to anger]
        with their idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now as for the rest of the acts of Omri which he did, and his might
        which he showed, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the
        Kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Omri slept with his fathers [in death] and was buried in Samaria.
        Ahab his son became king in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Ahab the son of Omri became king over Israel in the thirty-eighth
        year of Asa king of Judah, and Ahab the son of Omri reigned over Israel in
        Samaria for twenty-two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Ahab the son of Omri did evil in the sight of the Lord more than
        all [the kings] who were before him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'It came about, as if it had been a trivial thing for Ahab to walk
        in the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, that he married Jezebel the daughter
        of Ethbaal king of the Sidonians, and went and served Baal and worshiped
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So he erected an altar for Baal in the house of Baal which he built
        in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Ahab also made the Asherah. Ahab did more to provoke the Lord God
        of Israel than all the kings of Israel who were before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: In his days, Hiel the Bethelite rebuilt Jericho. He laid its foundations
        with the loss of Abiram his firstborn, and set up its gates with the loss
        of his youngest son Segub, in accordance with the word of the Lord, which
        He spoke through Joshua the son of Nun.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah Predicts Drought'
      title: Elijah Predicts Drought
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Elijah the Tishbite, who was of the settlers of Gilead, said
        to Ahab, \u201CAs the Lord, the God of Israel lives, before whom I stand,
        there shall be neither dew nor rain these years, except by my word.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the word of the Lord came to him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CGo from here and turn eastward and hide yourself by the brook
        Cherith, which is east of the Jordan [River]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You shall drink from the brook, and I have commanded the ravens to
        sustain you there [with food].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So he went and did in accordance with the word of the Lord; he went
        and lived by the brook Cherith, which is east of the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the ravens brought him bread and meat in the morning, and bread
        and meat in the evening; and he would drink from the brook. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'It happened after a while that the brook dried up, because there
        was no rain in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CArise, go to Zarephath, which belongs to Sidon, and stay there.
        Behold, I have commanded a widow there to provide for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So he set out and went to Zarephath, and when he came to the gate
        of the city, behold, a widow was there gathering sticks [for firewood]. He
        called out to her and said, \u201CPlease bring me a little water in a jar,
        so that I may drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "As she was going to get it, he called to her and said, \u201CPlease
        bring me a piece of bread in your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But she said, \u201CAs the Lord your God lives, I have no bread,
        only a handful of flour in the bowl and a little oil in the jar. See, I am
        gathering a few sticks so that I may go in and bake it for me and my son,
        that we may eat it [as our last meal] and die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Elijah said to her, \u201CDo not fear; go and do as you have said.
        Just make me a little bread from it first and bring it out to me, and afterward
        you may make one for yourself and for your son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For this is what the Lord God of Israel says: \u2018The bowl of flour
        shall not be exhausted nor shall the jar of oil be empty until the day that
        the Lord sends rain [again] on the face of the earth.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'She went and did as Elijah said. And she and he and her household
        ate for many days. '
      comments: []
    - name: "16: Elijah Raises the Widow\u2019s Son"
      title: "Elijah Raises the Widow\u2019s Son"
      number: 16
      content: 'The bowl of flour was not exhausted nor did the jar of oil become
        empty, in accordance with the word of the Lord which He spoke through Elijah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'It happened after these things, that the son of the woman, the mistress
        of the house, became sick; and his illness was so severe that there was no
        breath left in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So she said to Elijah, \u201CWhat [problem] is there between you
        and me, O man of God? Have you come to me to bring my sin to mind and to
        put my son to death?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He said to her, \u201CGive me your son.\u201D Then he took him from
        her arms and carried him up to the upper room where he was living, and laid
        him on his own bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He called to the Lord and said, \u201CO Lord my God, have You brought
        further tragedy to the widow with whom I am staying, by causing her son to
        die?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then he stretched himself out upon the child three times, and called
        to the Lord and said, \u201CO Lord my God, please let this child\u2019s life
        return to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The Lord heard the voice of Elijah, and the life of the child returned
        to him and he revived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Elijah took the child and brought him down from the upper room into
        the [lower part of the] house and gave him to his mother; and Elijah said,
        \u201CSee, your son is alive.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the woman said to Elijah, \u201CNow I know that you are a man
        of God and that the word of the Lord in your mouth is truth.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Obadiah Meets Elijah'
      title: Obadiah Meets Elijah
      number: 1
      content: "  Now it happened after many days that the word of the Lord came
        to Elijah in the third year, saying, \u201CGo, show yourself to Ahab, and
        I will send rain on the face of the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Elijah went to show himself to Ahab. Now the famine was severe
        in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Ahab called Obadiah who was the governor of his house. (Now Obadiah
        feared the Lord greatly; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'for when Jezebel destroyed the prophets of the Lord, Obadiah took
        a hundred prophets and hid them by fifties in a cave, and provided them with
        bread and water.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Ahab said to Obadiah, \u201CGo into the land to all the sources
        of water and to all the streams; perhaps we may find grass and keep the horses
        and mules alive, and not have to kill some of the cattle.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So they divided the land between them to survey it. Ahab went one
        way by himself and Obadiah went another way by himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "As Obadiah was on the way, behold, Elijah met him. He recognized
        him and fell face downward [out of respect] and said, \u201CIs it you, my
        lord Elijah?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "He answered him, \u201CIt is I. Go tell your master, \u2018Elijah
        is here.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But he said, \u201CWhat sin have I committed, that you would hand
        over your servant to Ahab to put me to death? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As the Lord your God lives, there is no nation or kingdom where my
        master has not sent messengers to seek you; and when they said, \u2018He
        is not here,\u2019 Ahab made the kingdom or nation swear that they had not
        found you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And now you are saying, \u2018Go, tell your master, \u201CBehold,
        Elijah [is here].\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And as soon as I leave you, the Spirit of the Lord will carry you
        to a place I do not know; so when I come to tell Ahab and he does not find
        you, he will kill me. Yet your servant has [reverently] feared the Lord from
        my youth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Has it not been told to my lord [Elijah] what I did when Jezebel
        killed the prophets of the Lord, how I hid a hundred of the Lord\u2019s prophets
        by fifties in a cave, and provided them with bread and water? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And now you are saying, \u2018Go, tell your master, \u201CElijah
        is here\u201D\u2009\u2019; and he will kill me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Elijah said, \u201CAs the Lord of hosts (armies) lives, before whom
        I stand, I will certainly show myself to Ahab today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Obadiah went to meet Ahab and told him; and Ahab went to meet
        Elijah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When Ahab saw Elijah, Ahab said to him, \u201CAre you the one who
        is bringing disaster on Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Elijah said, \u201CI have not brought disaster on Israel, but you
        and your father\u2019s household have, by abandoning (rejecting) the commandments
        of the Lord and by following the Baals. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: God or Baal on Mount Carmel'
      title: God or Baal on Mount Carmel
      number: 19
      content: "Now then, send word and gather to me all Israel at Mount Carmel,
        together with the 450 prophets of Baal and the 400 prophets of [the goddess]
        Asherah, who eat at [Queen] Jezebel\u2019s table.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Ahab sent word to all the Israelites and assembled the [pagan]
        prophets together at Mount Carmel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Elijah approached all the people and said, \u201CHow long will you
        hesitate between two opinions? If the Lord is God, follow Him; but if Baal,
        follow him.\u201D But the people [of Israel] did not answer him [so much
        as] a word. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Elijah said to the people, \u201CI alone remain a prophet of
        the Lord, while Baal\u2019s prophets are 450 men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now let them give us two oxen, and let them choose one ox for themselves
        and cut it in pieces, and lay it on the wood, but put no fire under it. I
        will prepare the other ox and lay it on the wood, and I will not put a fire
        under it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then you call on the name of your god, and I will call on the name
        of the Lord; and the god who answers by fire, He is God.\u201D And all the
        people answered, \u201CIt is well spoken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Elijah said to the prophets of Baal, \u201CChoose one bull for yourselves
        and prepare it first, since there are many of you; and call on the name of
        your god, but put no fire under it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So they took the bull that was given to them and prepared it, and
        called on the name of Baal from morning until noon, saying, \u201CO Baal,
        hear and answer us.\u201D But there was no voice and no one answered. And
        they leaped about the altar which they had made. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "At noon Elijah mocked them, saying, \u201CCry out with a loud voice,
        for he is a god; either he is occupied, or he is out [at the moment], or
        he is on a journey. Perhaps he is asleep and must be awakened!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So they cried out with a loud voice [to get Baal\u2019s attention]
        and cut themselves with swords and lances in accordance with their custom,
        until the blood flowed out on them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'As midday passed, they played the part of prophets and raved dramatically
        until the time for offering the evening sacrifice; but there was no voice,
        no one answered, and no one paid attention.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Elijah said to all the people, \u201CCome near to me.\u201D
        So all the people approached him. And he repaired and rebuilt the [old] altar
        of the Lord that had been torn down [by Jezebel]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Elijah took twelve stones in accordance with the number of the
        tribes of the sons of Jacob, to whom the word of the Lord had come, saying,
        \u201CIsrael shall be your name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So with the stones Elijah built an altar in the name of the Lord.
        He made a trench around the altar large enough to hold two measures of seed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then he laid out the wood and cut the ox in pieces and laid it on
        the wood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And he said, \u201CFill four pitchers with water and pour it on the
        burnt offering and the wood.\u201D And he said, \u201CDo it the second time.\u201D
        And they did it the second time. And he said, \u201CDo it the third time.\u201D
        And they did it a third time. "
      comments: []
    - name: "35: Elijah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Elijah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 35
      content: 'The water flowed around the altar, and he also filled the trench
        with water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "At the time of the offering of the evening sacrifice, Elijah the
        prophet approached [the altar] and said, \u201CO Lord, the God of Abraham,
        Isaac, and Israel (Jacob), let it be known today that You are God in Israel
        and that I am Your servant and that I have done all these things at Your
        word. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Answer me, O Lord, answer me, so that this people may know that You,
        O Lord, are God, and that You have turned their hearts back [to You].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then the fire of the Lord fell and consumed the burnt offering and
        the wood, and even the stones and the dust; it also licked up the water in
        the trench. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "When all the people saw it, they fell face downward; and they said,
        \u201CThe Lord, He is God! The Lord, He is God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then Elijah said to them, \u201CSeize the prophets of Baal; do not
        let one of them escape.\u201D They seized them; and Elijah brought them down
        to the brook Kishon, and [as God\u2019s law required] killed them there.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Now Elijah said to Ahab, \u201CGo up, eat and drink, for there is
        the sound of the roar of an abundance of rain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'So Ahab went up to eat and to drink. And Elijah went up to the top
        of Carmel; and he crouched down to the earth and put his face between his
        knees, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "and he said to his servant, \u201CGo up, look toward the sea.\u201D
        So he went up and looked and said, \u201CThere is nothing.\u201D Elijah said,
        \u201CGo back\u201D seven times. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "And at the seventh time the servant said, \u201CA cloud as small
        as a man\u2019s hand is coming up from the sea.\u201D And Elijah said, \u201CGo
        up, say to Ahab, \u2018Prepare your chariot and go down, so that the rain
        shower does not stop you.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'In a little while the sky grew dark with clouds and wind, and there
        were heavy showers. And Ahab mounted and rode [his chariot] and went [inland]
        to Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: Then the hand of the Lord came upon Elijah [giving him supernatural
        strength]. He girded up his loins and outran Ahab to the entrance of Jezreel
        [nearly twenty miles].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah Flees from Jezebel'
      title: Elijah Flees from Jezebel
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Ahab told Jezebel all that Elijah had done, and how he had
        killed all the prophets [of Baal] with the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Jezebel sent a messenger to Elijah, saying, \u201CSo may the
        gods do to me, and even more, if by this time tomorrow I do not make your
        life like the life of one of them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Elijah was afraid and arose and ran for his life, and he came
        to Beersheba which belongs to Judah, and he left his servant there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But he himself traveled a day\u2019s journey into the wilderness,
        and he came and sat down under a juniper tree and asked [God] that he might
        die. He said, \u201CIt is enough; now, O Lord, take my life, for I am no
        better than my fathers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He lay down and slept under the juniper tree, and behold, an angel
        touched him and said to him, \u201CGet up and eat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He looked, and by his head there was a bread cake baked on hot coal,
        and a pitcher of water. So he ate and drank and lay down again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the angel of the Lord came again a second time and touched him
        and said, \u201CGet up, and eat, for the journey is too long for you [without
        adequate sustenance].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Elijah at Horeb'
      title: Elijah at Horeb
      number: 8
      content: 'So he got up and ate and drank, and with the strength of that food
        he traveled forty days and nights to Horeb (Sinai), the mountain of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "There he came to a cave and spent the night in it; and behold, the
        word of the Lord  came to him, and He said to him, \u201CWhat are you doing
        here, Elijah?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He said, \u201CI have been very zealous (impassioned) for the Lord
        God of hosts (armies) [proclaiming what is rightfully and uniquely His];
        for the sons of Israel have abandoned (broken) Your covenant, torn down Your
        altars, and killed Your prophets with the sword. And I, only I, am left;
        and they seek to take away my life.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So He said, \u201CGo out and stand on the mountain before the Lord.\u201D
        And behold, the Lord was passing by, and a great and powerful wind was tearing
        out the mountains and breaking the rocks in pieces before the Lord; but the
        Lord was not in the wind. And after the wind, [there was] an earthquake,
        but the Lord was not in the earthquake. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'After the earthquake, [there was] a fire, but the Lord was not in
        the fire; and after the fire, [there was] the sound of a gentle blowing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When Elijah heard the sound, he wrapped his face in his mantle (cloak)
        and went out and stood in the entrance of the cave. And behold, a voice came
        to him and said, \u201CWhat are you doing here, Elijah?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He said, \u201CI have been very zealous for the Lord God of hosts
        (armies), because the sons of Israel have abandoned (broken) Your covenant,
        torn down Your altars and killed Your prophets with the sword. And I, only
        I, am left; and they seek to take away my life.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The Lord  said to him, \u201CGo, return on your way to the Wilderness
        of Damascus; and when you arrive, you shall anoint Hazael as king over Aram
        (Syria); "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and you shall anoint Jehu the son of Nimshi as king over Israel;
        and anoint Elisha the son of Shaphat of Abel-meholah as prophet in your place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'It shall come about that Jehu shall put to death whoever escapes
        from the sword of Hazael, and Elisha shall put to death whoever escapes the
        sword of Jehu. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Yet I will leave 7,000 [survivors] in Israel, all the knees that
        have not bowed down to Baal and every mouth that has not kissed him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Elijah departed from there and found Elisha the son of Shaphat,
        while he was plowing with twelve pairs of oxen before him, and he with the
        twelfth. Elijah went over to him and threw his mantle (coat) on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He left the oxen and ran after Elijah and said, \u201CPlease let
        me kiss my father and mother [goodbye], then I will follow you.\u201D And
        he said to him, \u201CGo on back; for what have I done to [stop] you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: So Elisha left him and went back. Then he took a pair of oxen and
        sacrificed them and boiled their meat with the implements of the oxen [as
        fuel], and gave the meat to the people, and they ate. Then he stood and followed
        Elijah, and served him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: War with Aram'
      title: War with Aram
      number: 1
      content: "  Ben-hadad king of Aram (Syria) gathered all his army together;
        thirty-two kings were [allied] with him, with horses and chariots. And he
        went up and besieged Samaria [Israel\u2019s capital], and fought against
        it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then he sent messengers to the city to Ahab king of Israel; and he
        said to him, \u201CThus says Ben-hadad: "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018Your silver and your gold are mine; your wives and your children,
        even the fairest, also are mine [as conditions of peace].\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The king of Israel [conceded his defeat and] answered, \u201CBy your
        word, my lord, O king, I am yours, and all that I have.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The messengers returned and said, \u201CThus says Ben-hadad: \u2018I
        indeed sent word to you, saying, \u201CYou shall give me your silver, your
        gold, your wives, and your children,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "but about this time tomorrow I will send my servants to you, and
        they will search your house and the houses of your servants; and they will
        take with their hands (confiscate) whatever is desirable in your eyes and
        carry it away.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the king of Israel summoned all the elders of the land and said,
        \u201CPlease observe and see how this man is seeking our destruction. For
        he sent messengers to me for my wives, my children, my silver, and my gold,
        and I did not refuse him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "All the elders and all the people said to him, \u201CDo not listen
        or consent [to this additional demand].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So he said to Ben-hadad\u2019s messengers, \u201CTell my lord the
        king, \u2018Every demand you first sent to your servant I will do, but I
        cannot do this [additional] thing [as a condition of peace].\u2019\u2009\u201D
        And the messengers left; then they brought him word again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Ben-hadad sent word to him and said, \u201CMay the gods do so to
        me, and more also, if there is enough dust left of Samaria for handfuls for
        all the [armed] people who follow me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The king of Israel answered, \u201CTell him, \u2018A man who puts
        on [his armor to go to battle] should not boast like the man who takes it
        off [after the battle has been won].\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Ahab Victorious'
      title: Ahab Victorious
      number: 12
      content: "When Ben-hadad heard this message, as he and the kings were drinking
        in the temporary shelters, he said to his servants, \u201CStation yourselves.\u201D
        So they stationed themselves against the city [of Samaria].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then a prophet approached Ahab king of Israel and said, \u201CThus
        says the Lord: \u2018Have you seen all this great army? Behold, I will hand
        them over to you, and you shall know [without any doubt] that I am the Lord.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Ahab said, \u201CBy whom?\u201D And he said, \u201CThus says the
        Lord: \u2018By the young men [the attendants or bodyguards] of the governors
        of the districts.\u2019\u2009\u201D Then Ahab said, \u201CWho shall begin
        the battle?\u201D And he answered, \u201CYou.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Ahab assembled and counted the young men of the governors of
        the districts, and there were 232. After them he assembled and counted all
        the people, all the sons of Israel, 7,000.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They went out at noon, while Ben-hadad was getting drunk in the temporary
        shelters, he and the thirty-two kings who were helping him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The young men of the governors of the districts went out first; and
        Ben-hadad sent men out and they told him, saying, \u201CMen have come out
        of Samaria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhether they have come out for peace or for war,
        take them alive.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So these young men of the governors of the districts went out of
        the city, and the army followed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And each one killed his man; and the Arameans (Syrians) fled and
        Israel pursued them. Ben-hadad king of Aram escaped on a horse with horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The king of Israel went out and struck [the riders of] the horses
        and chariots, and killed the Arameans in a great slaughter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the prophet approached the king of Israel and said to him, \u201CGo,
        strengthen yourself and observe and see what you have to do; for at the first
        of next year the king of Aram (Syria) will come up against you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now the servants of the king of Aram said to him, \u201CIsrael\u2019s
        god is a god of the hills; that is why they were stronger than we. But let
        us fight against them in the plain, and surely we will be stronger than they. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Do this: remove the [thirty-two allied] kings, each from his place,
        and put captains in their place, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Another Aramean War'
      title: Another Aramean War
      number: 25
      content: "and assemble an army like the army that you have lost in battle,
        horse for horse and chariot for chariot. Then we will fight against them
        in the plain, and surely we shall be stronger than they.\u201D And he listened
        to their words and did so.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'At the first of the year [in spring], Ben-hadad assembled and counted
        the Arameans (Syrians) and went up to Aphek [east of the Sea of Galilee]
        to fight against Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The sons of Israel were counted and given provisions, and they went
        to meet them. The Israelites camped before the enemy like two little flocks
        of goats [with everything against them, except God], and the Arameans filled
        the country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "A man of God approached and said to the king of Israel, \u201CThus
        says the Lord, \u2018Because the Arameans have said, \u201CThe Lord is a
        god of the hills, but He is not a god of the valleys,\u201D I will give this
        great army into your hand, and you shall know [by experience] that I am the
        Lord.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So they camped opposite each other for seven days. Then on the seventh
        day the battle began, and the sons of Israel killed 100,000 of the Aramean
        foot soldiers in a single day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'But the rest ran to the city of Aphek, and the [city] wall fell on
        27,000 of the men who were left. Ben-hadad escaped and came into the city,
        going into an inner chamber [to hide].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But his servants said to him, \u201CWe have heard that the kings
        of the house (royal line) of Israel are merciful kings. Please let us put
        sackcloth around our loins and ropes on our necks [as symbols of submission],
        and go out to the king of Israel; perhaps he will spare your life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "So they put sackcloth around their loins and ropes on their necks,
        and came to the king of Israel and said, \u201CYour servant Ben-hadad says,
        \u2018Please let me live.\u2019\u2009\u201D And Ahab asked, \u201CIs he still
        alive? He is my brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Now the men took it as a good omen, and quickly understanding his
        meaning said, \u201CYes, your brother Ben-hadad lives.\u201D Then the king
        said, \u201CGo, bring him.\u201D Then Ben-hadad came out to him, and Ahab
        had him come up into the chariot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Ben-hadad [tempting him] said to him, \u201CI will restore the cities
        which my father took from your father; and you may set up bazaars (shops)
        of your own in Damascus, as my father did in Samaria.\u201D Then, Ahab replied,
        \u201CI will let you go with this covenant (treaty).\u201D So he made a covenant
        with him and let him go.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Now a certain man of the sons of the prophets said to another by
        the word of the Lord, \u201CPlease strike me.\u201D But the man refused to
        strike him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then the prophet said to him, \u201CBecause you have not obeyed the
        voice of the Lord, behold, as soon as you leave me, a lion will kill you.\u201D
        And as soon as he left him, a lion found him and killed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then the prophet found another man and said, \u201CPlease strike
        me.\u201D So the man struck him hard, wounding him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So the prophet left and waited for King Ahab by the road, and disguised
        himself [as a wounded soldier] with a bandage over his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "As the king passed by, the prophet called out to the king and said,
        \u201CYour servant went out into the middle of the battle, and behold, a
        man turned aside and brought a man to me and said, \u2018Guard this man;
        if for any reason he is missing, then your life shall be required for his
        life, or else you shall pay a talent of silver.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "But while your servant was busy here and there, he [escaped and]
        was gone.\u201D And the king of Israel said to him, \u201CSuch is your own
        judgment (verdict); you have determined it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then the prophet quickly removed the bandage from his eyes, and [Ahab]
        the king of Israel recognized him as one of the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "He said to the king, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Because you
        have released from your hand the man [Ben-hadad] whom I had devoted to destruction,
        your life shall be required for his life, and your people for his people.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: So the king of Israel went to his house resentful and sullen, and
        came to Samaria.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Ahab Covets Naboth\u2019s Vineyard"
      title: "Ahab Covets Naboth\u2019s Vineyard"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it came about after these things that Naboth the Jezreelite
        had a vineyard in Jezreel, close beside the [winter] palace of Ahab king
        of Samaria; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Ahab spoke to Naboth, saying, \u201CGive me your vineyard, so that
        I may have it for a garden of vegetables and herbs, because it is near my
        house. I will give you a better vineyard for it, or, if you prefer, I will
        give you what it is worth in money.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Naboth said to Ahab, \u201CThe Lord forbid me that I should give
        the inheritance of my fathers to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Ahab [already upset by the Lord\u2019s message] came into his
        house [feeling more] resentful and sullen because of what Naboth the Jezreelite
        had said to him; for he had said, \u201CI will not give you the inheritance
        of my fathers.\u201D And he lay down on his bed and turned away his face,
        and would not eat any food.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Jezebel his wife came to him and asked him, \u201CWhy is your
        spirit so troubled that you have not eaten?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he said to her, \u201CBecause I spoke to Naboth the Jezreelite
        and said to him, \u2018Give me your vineyard for money; or if you prefer,
        I will give you another vineyard for it.\u2019 But he answered, \u2018I will
        not give you my vineyard.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jezebel his wife said to him, \u201CDo you now reign over Israel?
        Get up, eat food, and let your heart rejoice; I will give you the vineyard
        of Naboth the Jezreelite.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So she wrote letters in Ahab\u2019s name and sealed them with his
        seal, and sent them to the elders and nobles who lived with Naboth in his
        city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now in the letters she wrote, \u201CProclaim a fast and seat Naboth
        at the head of the people; "
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Jezebel\u2019s Plot"
      title: "Jezebel\u2019s Plot"
      number: 10
      content: "and seat two worthless and unprincipled men opposite him, and have
        them testify against him, saying, \u2018You cursed God and the king.\u2019
        Then take him out and stone him to death.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So the men of his city, the elders and the nobles who lived there,
        did as Jezebel had sent word to them, just as it was written in the letters
        which she had sent to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They proclaimed a fast and seated Naboth at the head of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Two worthless and unprincipled men came in and sat down opposite
        him; and they testified against Naboth before the people, saying, \u201CNaboth
        cursed and renounced God and the king.\u201D Then they brought him outside
        the city and stoned him to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then they sent word to Jezebel, saying, \u201CNaboth has been stoned
        to death.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When Jezebel heard that Naboth had been stoned and was dead, she
        said to Ahab, \u201CArise, take possession of the vineyard of Naboth the
        Jezreelite which he refused to sell you, because Naboth is no longer alive,
        but dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When Ahab heard that Naboth was dead, he arose to go down to the
        vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, to take possession of it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to Elijah the Tishbite, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CArise, go down to meet Ahab king of Israel, who is in Samaria.
        Behold, he is in the vineyard of Naboth, where he has gone to take possession
        of it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "You shall speak to him, saying, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CHave
        you murdered and also taken possession [of the victim\u2019s property]?\u201D\u2009\u2019
        And you shall speak to him, saying, \u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CIn the
        place where dogs licked up the blood of Naboth, dogs will lick up your blood
        as well.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Ahab said to Elijah, \u201CHave you found me, O my enemy?\u201D And
        he answered, \u201CI have found you, because you have sold yourself to do
        evil in the sight of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Behold [says the Lord], I am bringing evil (catastrophe) on you,
        and will utterly sweep you away, and will cut off from Ahab every male, both
        bond and free in Israel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and I will make your house (descendants) like that of Jeroboam the
        son of Nebat, and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah, for provoking
        Me to anger and making Israel sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "The Lord also spoke in regard to Jezebel, saying, \u2018The dogs
        will eat [the body of] Jezebel in the district of Jezreel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The dogs will eat anyone belonging to Ahab who dies in the city,
        and the birds of the air will eat anyone who dies in the field.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'There certainly was no one like Ahab who sold himself to do evil
        in the sight of the Lord, because Jezebel his wife incited him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He acted very repulsively in following idols, in accordance with
        everything the Amorites had done, whom the Lord expelled [from the land]
        before the sons of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now when Ahab heard these words [of Elijah], he tore his clothes,
        put on sackcloth and fasted, and he lay in sackcloth and went about dejectedly
        (mourning). '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to Elijah the Tishbite, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CDo you see how Ahab has humbled himself before Me? Because
        he has humbled himself before Me, I will not bring the evil (catastrophe)
        in his lifetime, but in his son\u2019s days I will bring evil upon his house.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Ahab\u2019s Third Campaign against Aram"
      title: "Ahab\u2019s Third Campaign against Aram"
      number: 1
      content: '  Aram (Syria) and Israel continued without war for three years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In the third year Jehoshaphat king of Judah came down to the king
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now the king of Israel said to his servants, \u201CDo you know that
        Ramoth in Gilead is ours, yet we are still doing nothing to take it from
        the hand of the king of Aram?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Ahab said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CWill you go with me to battle
        at Ramoth-gilead?\u201D Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, \u201CI am
        as you are, my people as your people, my horses as your horses.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, \u201CPlease inquire
        first for the word of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the king of Israel gathered the prophets together, about four
        hundred men, and said to them, \u201CShall I go to battle against Ramoth-gilead,
        or should I not?\u201D And they said, \u201CGo up, for the Lord has handed
        it over to the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But Jehoshaphat [doubted and] said, \u201CIs there not another prophet
        of the Lord here whom we may ask?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CThere is one more man,
        Micaiah the son of Imlah, by whom we may inquire of the Lord, but I hate
        him, because he never prophesies good news for me, but only evil.\u201D But
        Jehoshaphat said, \u201CMay the king not say that [Micaiah only tells bad
        news].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the king of Israel summoned an officer and said, \u201CBring
        quickly Micaiah the son of Imlah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah were each sitting
        on his throne, dressed in their [royal] robes, [in an open place] at the
        threshing floor at the entrance of the gate of Samaria; and all the prophets
        were prophesying before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah made for himself horns of iron
        and said, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018With these you will gore the Arameans
        (Syrians) until they are destroyed.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Micaiah Predicts Defeat'
      title: Micaiah Predicts Defeat
      number: 12
      content: "All the prophets were prophesying in the same way [to please Ahab],
        saying, \u201CGo up to Ramoth-gilead and be successful, for the Lord will
        hand it over to the king.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the messenger who went to summon Micaiah said to him, \u201CListen
        carefully, the words of the prophets are unanimously favorable to the king.
        Please let your words be like the word of one of them, and speak favorably.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Micaiah said, \u201CAs the Lord lives, I will speak what the
        Lord says to me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So when he came to the king, the king said to him, \u201CMicaiah,
        shall we go against Ramoth-gilead in battle, or shall we not?\u201D And he
        answered him, \u201CGo up and be successful, for the Lord will hand it over
        to the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But the king [doubted him and] said to him, \u201CHow many times
        must I make you swear to tell me nothing but the truth in the name of the
        Lord?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said,\u201CI saw all IsraelScattered upon the mountains,Like
        sheep that have no shepherd.And the Lord said,\u2018These have no master.Let
        each of them return to his house in peace.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CDid I not tell
        you that he would not prophesy good concerning me, but evil?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Micaiah said, \u201CTherefore, hear the word of the Lord. I saw the
        Lord sitting on His throne, and all the host (army) of heaven standing by
        Him on His right hand and on His left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The Lord said, \u2018Who will entice Ahab to go up and fall at Ramoth-gilead?\u2019
        And one said this, while another said that. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then a spirit came forward and stood before the Lord and said, \u2018I
        will entice him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The Lord said to him, \u2018How?\u2019 And he said, \u2018I will
        go out and be a deceiving spirit in the mouth of all his prophets.\u2019
        Then the Lord said, \u2018You are to entice him and also succeed. Go and
        do so.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now then, behold, the Lord has put a deceiving spirit in the mouth
        of all these prophets; and the Lord has proclaimed disaster against you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah approached and struck Micaiah on
        the cheek and said, \u201CHow did the Spirit of the Lord pass from me to
        speak to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Micaiah said, \u201CBehold, you shall see on that day [of the king\u2019s
        defeat] when you enter an inner room [looking for a place] to hide yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then the king of Israel said, \u201CTake Micaiah and return him to
        Amon, the governor of the city, and to Joash, the king\u2019s son, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "and say, \u2018Thus says the king, \u201CPut this man in prison,
        and feed him sparingly with the bread and water until I return safely.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Defeat and Death of Ahab'
      title: Defeat and Death of Ahab
      number: 28
      content: "Micaiah said, \u201CIf you indeed return safely, the Lord has not
        spoken by me.\u201D Then he said, \u201CListen, all you people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So [Ahab] the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah went
        up to Ramoth-gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CI will disguise myself
        and enter the battle, but you put on your [royal] clothing.\u201D So the
        king of Israel disguised himself and went into the battle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Now the king of Aram (Syria) had commanded the thirty-two captains
        of his chariots, saying, \u201CDo not fight with [anyone, either] small or
        great, but with [Ahab] the king of Israel alone.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "When the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat, they said, \u201CSurely
        it is the king of Israel.\u201D They turned to fight against him, and Jehoshaphat
        shouted out [in fear]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When the captains of the chariots saw that it was not the king of
        Israel, they turned back from pursuing him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But one man drew a bow at random and struck the king of Israel in
        a joint of the armor. So he said to the driver of his chariot, \u201CTurn
        around and take me out of the fight, because I have been seriously wounded.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The battle raged that day, and [Ahab] the king was propped up in
        his chariot facing the Arameans (Syrians). And in the evening he died, and
        the blood from his wound ran down into the bottom of the chariot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then about sundown a resounding cry passed throughout the army, saying,
        \u201CEvery man to his city and every man to his own country!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'So the king died and was brought to Samaria, and they buried the
        king in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'They washed the chariot by the pool [on the outskirts] of Samaria,
        where the prostitutes bathed, and the dogs licked up his blood, in accordance
        with the word of the Lord which He had spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Now the rest of Ahab\u2019s acts, and everything that he did, the
        ivory palace which he built and all the cities which he built, are they not
        written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: The New Rulers'
      title: The New Rulers
      number: 40
      content: 'So Ahab slept with his fathers [in death], and Ahaziah his son became
        king in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Now Jehoshaphat the son of Asa became king over Judah in the fourth
        year of Ahab king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Jehoshaphat was thirty-five years old when he became king, and he
        reigned twenty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Azubah
        the daughter of Shilhi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'He walked in all the ways of Asa his father, without turning from
        them, doing right in the sight of the Lord. However, the high places were
        not removed; the people still sacrificed and burned incense on the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Jehoshaphat also made peace with the king of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, his might which he displayed
        and how he made war, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of
        the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'And the remnant of the sodomites (male cult prostitutes) who remained
        in the days of his father Asa, Jehoshaphat expelled from the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Now there was no king in Edom; a deputy (governor) was [serving as]
        king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Jehoshaphat had [large cargo] ships of Tarshish constructed to go
        to Ophir for gold, but they did not go, because the ships were wrecked at
        Ezion-geber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Then Ahaziah the son of Ahab said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CLet my servants
        go with your servants in the ships,\u201D But Jehoshaphat was unwilling and
        refused. "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers [in death] and was buried with
        his fathers in the city of his father David, and Jehoram his son became king
        in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Ahaziah the son of Ahab became king over Israel in Samaria in the
        seventeenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and he reigned over Israel
        for two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord and walked in the [idolatrous]
        way of his father [Ahab] and of his mother [Jezebel], and in the way of Jeroboam
        the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: He served Baal and worshiped him, and he provoked the Lord God of
        Israel to anger, in accordance with everything that his father [Ahab] had
        done.
      comments: []
